230 #define NLOHMANN_JSON_HAS_HELPER(type) \
231  template<typename T> struct has_##type { \
232  private: \
233  template<typename U, typename = typename U::type> \
234  static int detect(U &&); \
235  static void detect(...); \
236  public: \
237  static constexpr bool value = \
238  std::is_integral<decltype(detect(std::declval<T>()))>::value; \

283 // implementation of C++14 index_sequence and affiliates
284 // source: https://stackoverflow.com/a/32223343
285 template<std::size_t... Ints>
286 struct index_sequence
287 {
288  using type = index_sequence;
289  using value_type = std::size_t;
290  static constexpr std::size_t size() noexcept
291  {
292  return sizeof...(Ints);
293  }
294 };

296 template<class Sequence1, class Sequence2>
297 struct merge_and_renumber;
298 
299 template<std::size_t... I1, std::size_t... I2>
300 struct merge_and_renumber<index_sequence<I1...>, index_sequence<I2...>>
301  : index_sequence < I1..., (sizeof...(I1) + I2)... > {};
302 
303 template<std::size_t N>
304 struct make_index_sequence
305  : merge_and_renumber < typename make_index_sequence < N / 2 >::type,
306  typename make_index_sequence < N - N / 2 >::type > {};
307 
308 template<> struct make_index_sequence<0> : index_sequence<> {};
309 template<> struct make_index_sequence<1> : index_sequence<0> {};
310 
311 template<typename... Ts>
312 using index_sequence_for = make_index_sequence<sizeof...(Ts)>;

314 /*
315 Implementation of two C++17 constructs: conjunction, negation. This is needed
316 to avoid evaluating all the traits in a condition
317 
318 For example: not std::is_same<void, T>::value and has_value_type<T>::value
319 will not compile when T = void (on MSVC at least). Whereas
320 conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, T>>, has_value_type<T>>::value will
321 stop evaluating if negation<...>::value == false
322 
323 Please note that those constructs must be used with caution, since symbols can
324 become very long quickly (which can slow down compilation and cause MSVC
325 internal compiler errors). Only use it when you have to (see example ahead).
326 */
327 template<class...> struct conjunction : std::true_type {};
328 template<class B1> struct conjunction<B1> : B1 {};
329 template<class B1, class... Bn>
330 struct conjunction<B1, Bn...> : std::conditional<bool(B1::value), conjunction<Bn...>, B1>::type {};
331 
332 template<class B> struct negation : std::integral_constant<bool, not B::value> {};
333 
334 // dispatch utility (taken from ranges-v3)
335 template<unsigned N> struct priority_tag : priority_tag < N - 1 > {};
336 template<> struct priority_tag<0> {};

355 template<bool B, class RealType, class CompatibleObjectType>
356 struct is_compatible_object_type_impl : std::false_type {};
357 
358 template<class RealType, class CompatibleObjectType>
359 struct is_compatible_object_type_impl<true, RealType, CompatibleObjectType>
360 {
361  static constexpr auto value =
362  std::is_constructible<typename RealType::key_type, typename CompatibleObjectType::key_type>::value and
363  std::is_constructible<typename RealType::mapped_type, typename CompatibleObjectType::mapped_type>::value;
364 };
365 
366 template<bool B, class RealType, class CompatibleStringType>
367 struct is_compatible_string_type_impl : std::false_type {};
368 
369 template<class RealType, class CompatibleStringType>
370 struct is_compatible_string_type_impl<true, RealType, CompatibleStringType>
371 {
372  static constexpr auto value =
373  std::is_same<typename RealType::value_type, typename CompatibleStringType::value_type>::value and
374  std::is_constructible<RealType, CompatibleStringType>::value;
375 };
376 
377 template<class BasicJsonType, class CompatibleObjectType>
378 struct is_compatible_object_type
379 {
380  static auto constexpr value = is_compatible_object_type_impl <
381  conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, CompatibleObjectType>>,
382  has_mapped_type<CompatibleObjectType>,
383  has_key_type<CompatibleObjectType>>::value,
384  typename BasicJsonType::object_t, CompatibleObjectType >::value;
385 };
386 
387 template<class BasicJsonType, class CompatibleStringType>
388 struct is_compatible_string_type
389 {
390  static auto constexpr value = is_compatible_string_type_impl <
391  conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, CompatibleStringType>>,
392  has_value_type<CompatibleStringType>>::value,
393  typename BasicJsonType::string_t, CompatibleStringType >::value;
394 };
395 
396 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
397 struct is_basic_json_nested_type
398 {
399  static auto constexpr value = std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::iterator>::value or
400  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::const_iterator>::value or
401  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::reverse_iterator>::value or
402  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::const_reverse_iterator>::value;
403 };
404 
405 template<class BasicJsonType, class CompatibleArrayType>
406 struct is_compatible_array_type
407 {
408  static auto constexpr value =
409  conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, CompatibleArrayType>>,
410  negation<is_compatible_object_type<
411  BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType>>,
412  negation<std::is_constructible<typename BasicJsonType::string_t,
413  CompatibleArrayType>>,
414  negation<is_basic_json_nested_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType>>,
415  has_value_type<CompatibleArrayType>,
416  has_iterator<CompatibleArrayType>>::value;
417 };
418 
419 template<bool, typename, typename>
420 struct is_compatible_integer_type_impl : std::false_type {};
421 
422 template<typename RealIntegerType, typename CompatibleNumberIntegerType>
423 struct is_compatible_integer_type_impl<true, RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType>
424 {
425  // is there an assert somewhere on overflows?
426  using RealLimits = std::numeric_limits<RealIntegerType>;
427  using CompatibleLimits = std::numeric_limits<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>;
428 
429  static constexpr auto value =
430  std::is_constructible<RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value and
431  CompatibleLimits::is_integer and
432  RealLimits::is_signed == CompatibleLimits::is_signed;
433 };
434 
435 template<typename RealIntegerType, typename CompatibleNumberIntegerType>
436 struct is_compatible_integer_type
437 {
438  static constexpr auto value =
439  is_compatible_integer_type_impl <
440  std::is_integral<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value and
441  not std::is_same<bool, CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value,
442  RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType > ::value;
443 };

445 // trait checking if JSONSerializer<T>::from_json(json const&, udt&) exists
446 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
447 struct has_from_json
448 {
449  private:
450  // also check the return type of from_json
451  template<typename U, typename = enable_if_t<std::is_same<void, decltype(uncvref_t<U>::from_json(
452  std::declval<BasicJsonType>(), std::declval<T&>()))>::value>>
453  static int detect(U&&);
454  static void detect(...);
455 
456  public:
457  static constexpr bool value = std::is_integral<decltype(
458  detect(std::declval<typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>>()))>::value;
459 };
460 
461 // This trait checks if JSONSerializer<T>::from_json(json const&) exists
462 // this overload is used for non-default-constructible user-defined-types
463 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
464 struct has_non_default_from_json
465 {
466  private:
467  template <
468  typename U,
469  typename = enable_if_t<std::is_same<
470  T, decltype(uncvref_t<U>::from_json(std::declval<BasicJsonType>()))>::value >>
471  static int detect(U&&);
472  static void detect(...);
473 
474  public:
475  static constexpr bool value = std::is_integral<decltype(detect(
476  std::declval<typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>>()))>::value;
477 };
478 
479 // This trait checks if BasicJsonType::json_serializer<T>::to_json exists
480 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
481 struct has_to_json
482 {
483  private:
484  template<typename U, typename = decltype(uncvref_t<U>::to_json(
485  std::declval<BasicJsonType&>(), std::declval<T>()))>
486  static int detect(U&&);
487  static void detect(...);
488 
489  public:
490  static constexpr bool value = std::is_integral<decltype(detect(
491  std::declval<typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>>()))>::value;
492 };
493 
494 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleCompleteType>
495 struct is_compatible_complete_type
496 {
497  static constexpr bool value =
498  not std::is_base_of<std::istream, CompatibleCompleteType>::value and
499  not is_basic_json<CompatibleCompleteType>::value and
500  not is_basic_json_nested_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleCompleteType>::value and
501  has_to_json<BasicJsonType, CompatibleCompleteType>::value;
502 };
503 
504 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleType>
505 struct is_compatible_type
506  : conjunction<is_complete_type<CompatibleType>,
507  is_compatible_complete_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleType>>
508 {
509 };

566 class exception : public std::exception
567 {
568  public:
570  const char* what() const noexcept override
571  {
572  return m.what();
573  }
574 
576  const int id;
577 
578  protected:
579  exception(int id_, const char* what_arg) : id(id_), m(what_arg) {}
580 
581  static std::string name(const std::string& ename, int id_)
582  {
583  return "[json.exception." + ename + "." + std::to_string(id_) + "] ";
584  }
585 
586  private:
588  std::runtime_error m;
589 };
590 
634 class parse_error : public exception
635 {
636  public:
645  static parse_error create(int id_, std::size_t byte_, const std::string& what_arg)
646  {
647  std::string w = exception::name("parse_error", id_) + "parse error" +
648  (byte_ != 0 ? (" at " + std::to_string(byte_)) : "") +
649  ": " + what_arg;
650  return parse_error(id_, byte_, w.c_str());
651  }
652 
662  const std::size_t byte;
663 
664  private:
665  parse_error(int id_, std::size_t byte_, const char* what_arg)
666  : exception(id_, what_arg), byte(byte_) {}
667 };
668

863 namespace nlohmann
864 {
865 namespace detail
866 {
868 // JSON type enumeration //
870 
895 enum class value_t : std::uint8_t
896 {
897  null,
898  object,
899  array,
900  string,
901  boolean,
902  number_integer,
903  number_unsigned,
904  number_float,
905  discarded
906 };
907 
918 inline bool operator<(const value_t lhs, const value_t rhs) noexcept
919 {
920  static constexpr std::array<std::uint8_t, 8> order = {{
921  0 /* null */, 3 /* object */, 4 /* array */, 5 /* string */,
922  1 /* boolean */, 2 /* integer */, 2 /* unsigned */, 2 /* float */
923  }
924  };
925 
926  const auto l_index = static_cast<std::size_t>(lhs);
927  const auto r_index = static_cast<std::size_t>(rhs);
928  return l_index < order.size() and r_index < order.size() and order[l_index] < order[r_index];
929 }
930 }
931 }

962 template<typename BasicJsonType>
963 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename std::nullptr_t& n)
964 {
965  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_null()))
966  {
967  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be null, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
968  }
969  n = nullptr;
970 }
971 
972 // overloads for basic_json template parameters
973 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
974  enable_if_t<std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
975  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
976  int> = 0>
977 void get_arithmetic_value(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val)
978 {
979  switch (static_cast<value_t>(j))
980  {
981  case value_t::number_unsigned:
982  {
983  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
984  break;
985  }
986  case value_t::number_integer:
987  {
988  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
989  break;
990  }
991  case value_t::number_float:
992  {
993  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
994  break;
995  }
996 
997  default:
998  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
999  }
1000 }
1001 
1002 template<typename BasicJsonType>
1003 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t& b)
1004 {
1005  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_boolean()))
1006  {
1007  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be boolean, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1008  }
1009  b = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t*>();
1010 }

1015  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_string()))
1016  {
1017  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be string, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1018  }
1019  s = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::string_t*>();
1020 }

1024  enable_if_t <
1025  is_compatible_string_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleStringType>::value and
1026  not std::is_same<typename BasicJsonType::string_t,
1027  CompatibleStringType>::value,
1028  int > = 0 >
1029 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleStringType& s)
1030 {
1031  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_string()))
1032  {
1033  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be string, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1034  }
1035 
1036  s = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::string_t*>();
1037 }

1057 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename EnumType,
1058  enable_if_t<std::is_enum<EnumType>::value, int> = 0>
1059 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, EnumType& e)
1060 {
1061  typename std::underlying_type<EnumType>::type val;
1062  get_arithmetic_value(j, val);
1063  e = static_cast<EnumType>(val);

1066 template<typename BasicJsonType>
1067 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::array_t& arr)
1068 {
1069  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1070  {
1071  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1072  }
1073  arr = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::array_t*>();
1074 }

1076 // forward_list doesn't have an insert method
1077 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename Allocator,
1078  enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<BasicJsonType, T>::value, int> = 0>
1079 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::forward_list<T, Allocator>& l)
1080 {
1081  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1082  {
1083  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1084  }
1085  std::transform(j.rbegin(), j.rend(),
1086  std::front_inserter(l), [](const BasicJsonType & i)
1087  {
1088  return i.template get<T>();
1089  });
1090 }
1091 
1092 // valarray doesn't have an insert method
1093 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T,
1094  enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<BasicJsonType, T>::value, int> = 0>
1095 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::valarray<T>& l)
1096 {
1097  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1098  {
1099  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1100  }
1101  l.resize(j.size());
1102  std::copy(j.m_value.array->begin(), j.m_value.array->end(), std::begin(l));
1103 }
1104 
1105 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType>
1106 void from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleArrayType& arr, priority_tag<0> /*unused*/)
1107 {
1108  using std::end;
1109 
1110  std::transform(j.begin(), j.end(),
1111  std::inserter(arr, end(arr)), [](const BasicJsonType & i)
1112  {
1113  // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
1114  // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
1115  return i.template get<typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>();
1116  });
1117 }
1118 
1119 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType>
1120 auto from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleArrayType& arr, priority_tag<1> /*unused*/)
1121 -> decltype(
1122  arr.reserve(std::declval<typename CompatibleArrayType::size_type>()),
1123  void())
1124 {
1125  using std::end;
1126 
1127  arr.reserve(j.size());
1128  std::transform(j.begin(), j.end(),
1129  std::inserter(arr, end(arr)), [](const BasicJsonType & i)
1130  {
1131  // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
1132  // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
1133  return i.template get<typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>();
1134  });
1135 }
1136 
1137 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T, std::size_t N>
1138 void from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, std::array<T, N>& arr, priority_tag<2> /*unused*/)
1139 {
1140  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < N; ++i)
1141  {
1142  arr[i] = j.at(i).template get<T>();
1143  }
1144 }

1146 template <
1147  typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType,
1148  enable_if_t <
1149  is_compatible_array_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType>::value and
1150  not std::is_same<typename BasicJsonType::array_t,
1151  CompatibleArrayType>::value and
1152  std::is_constructible <
1153  BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type >::value,
1154  int > = 0 >
1155 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleArrayType& arr)
1156 {
1157  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1158  {
1159  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " +
1160  std::string(j.type_name())));
1161  }
1162 
1163  from_json_array_impl(j, arr, priority_tag<2> {});
1164 }

1166 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleObjectType,
1167  enable_if_t<is_compatible_object_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleObjectType>::value, int> = 0>
1168 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleObjectType& obj)
1169 {
1170  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_object()))
1171  {
1172  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be object, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1173  }
1174 
1175  auto inner_object = j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::object_t*>();
1176  using value_type = typename CompatibleObjectType::value_type;
1177  std::transform(
1178  inner_object->begin(), inner_object->end(),
1179  std::inserter(obj, obj.begin()),
1180  [](typename BasicJsonType::object_t::value_type const & p)
1181  {
1182  return value_type(p.first, p.second.template get<typename CompatibleObjectType::mapped_type>());
1183  });
1184 }
1185 
1186 // overload for arithmetic types, not chosen for basic_json template arguments
1187 // (BooleanType, etc..); note: Is it really necessary to provide explicit
1188 // overloads for boolean_t etc. in case of a custom BooleanType which is not
1189 // an arithmetic type?
1190 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
1191  enable_if_t <
1192  std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
1193  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t>::value and
1194  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t>::value and
1195  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t>::value and
1196  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
1197  int> = 0>
1198 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val)
1199 {
1200  switch (static_cast<value_t>(j))
1201  {
1202  case value_t::number_unsigned:
1203  {
1204  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
1205  break;
1206  }
1207  case value_t::number_integer:
1208  {
1209  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
1210  break;
1211  }
1212  case value_t::number_float:
1213  {
1214  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
1215  break;
1216  }
1217  case value_t::boolean:
1218  {
1219  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t*>());
1220  break;
1221  }
1222 
1223  default:
1224  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1225  }
1226 }
1227 
1228 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename A1, typename A2>
1229 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::pair<A1, A2>& p)
1230 {
1231  p = {j.at(0).template get<A1>(), j.at(1).template get<A2>()};
1232 }

1234 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename Tuple, std::size_t... Idx>
1235 void from_json_tuple_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, Tuple& t, index_sequence<Idx...>)
1236 {
1237  t = std::make_tuple(j.at(Idx).template get<typename std::tuple_element<Idx, Tuple>::type>()...);
1238 }
1239 
1240 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename... Args>
1241 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::tuple<Args...>& t)
1242 {
1243  from_json_tuple_impl(j, t, index_sequence_for<Args...> {});
1244 }

1246 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename Key, typename Value, typename Compare, typename Allocator,
1247  typename = enable_if_t<not std::is_constructible<
1248  typename BasicJsonType::string_t, Key>::value>>
1249 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::map<Key, Value, Compare, Allocator>& m)
1250 {
1251  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1252  {
1253  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1254  }
1255  for (const auto& p : j)
1256  {
1257  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not p.is_array()))
1258  {
1259  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(p.type_name())));
1260  }
1261  m.emplace(p.at(0).template get<Key>(), p.at(1).template get<Value>());
1262  }
1263 }
1264 
1265 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename Key, typename Value, typename Hash, typename KeyEqual, typename Allocator,
1266  typename = enable_if_t<not std::is_constructible<
1267  typename BasicJsonType::string_t, Key>::value>>
1268 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::unordered_map<Key, Value, Hash, KeyEqual, Allocator>& m)
1269 {
1270  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1271  {
1272  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1273  }
1274  for (const auto& p : j)
1275  {
1276  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not p.is_array()))
1277  {
1278  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(p.type_name())));
1279  }
1280  m.emplace(p.at(0).template get<Key>(), p.at(1).template get<Value>());
1281  }
1282 }
1283 
1284 struct from_json_fn
1285 {
1286  private:
1287  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1288  auto call(const BasicJsonType& j, T& val, priority_tag<1> /*unused*/) const
1289  noexcept(noexcept(from_json(j, val)))
1290  -> decltype(from_json(j, val), void())
1291  {
1292  return from_json(j, val);
1293  }
1294 
1295  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1296  void call(const BasicJsonType& /*unused*/, T& /*unused*/, priority_tag<0> /*unused*/) const noexcept
1297  {
1298  static_assert(sizeof(BasicJsonType) == 0,
1299  "could not find from_json() method in T's namespace");
1300 #ifdef _MSC_VER
1301  // MSVC does not show a stacktrace for the above assert
1302  using decayed = uncvref_t<T>;
1303  static_assert(sizeof(typename decayed::force_msvc_stacktrace) == 0,
1304  "forcing MSVC stacktrace to show which T we're talking about.");
1305 #endif
1306  }
1307 
1308  public:
1309  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1310  void operator()(const BasicJsonType& j, T& val) const
1311  noexcept(noexcept(std::declval<from_json_fn>().call(j, val, priority_tag<1> {})))
1312  {
1313  return call(j, val, priority_tag<1> {});
1314  }
1315 };
1316 }
1317 
1321 namespace
1322 {
1323 constexpr const auto& from_json = detail::static_const<detail::from_json_fn>::value;
1324 }
1325 }

1352 namespace nlohmann
1353 {
1354 namespace detail
1355 {
1357 template<typename IteratorType> class iteration_proxy
1358 {
1359  private:
1361  class iteration_proxy_internal
1362  {
1363  public:
1364  using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
1365  using value_type = iteration_proxy_internal;
1366  using pointer = iteration_proxy_internal*;
1367  using reference = iteration_proxy_internal&;
1368  using iterator_category = std::input_iterator_tag;
1369 
1370  private:
1372  IteratorType anchor;
1374  std::size_t array_index = 0;
1376  mutable std::size_t array_index_last = 0;
1378  mutable std::string array_index_str = "0";
1380  const std::string empty_str = "";
1381 
1382  public:
1383  explicit iteration_proxy_internal(IteratorType it) noexcept : anchor(it) {}
1384 
1385  iteration_proxy_internal(const iteration_proxy_internal&) = default;
1386  iteration_proxy_internal& operator=(const iteration_proxy_internal&) = default;
1387 
1389  iteration_proxy_internal& operator*()
1390  {
1391  return *this;
1392  }
1393 
1395  iteration_proxy_internal& operator++()
1396  {
1397  ++anchor;
1398  ++array_index;
1399 
1400  return *this;
1401  }
1402 
1404  bool operator==(const iteration_proxy_internal& o) const noexcept
1405  {
1406  return anchor == o.anchor;
1407  }
1408 
1410  bool operator!=(const iteration_proxy_internal& o) const noexcept
1411  {
1412  return anchor != o.anchor;
1413  }
1414 
1416  const std::string& key() const
1417  {
1418  assert(anchor.m_object != nullptr);
1419 
1420  switch (anchor.m_object->type())
1421  {
1422  // use integer array index as key
1423  case value_t::array:
1424  {
1425  if (array_index != array_index_last)
1426  {
1427  array_index_str = std::to_string(array_index);
1428  array_index_last = array_index;
1429  }
1430  return array_index_str;
1431  }
1432 
1433  // use key from the object
1434  case value_t::object:
1435  return anchor.key();
1436 
1437  // use an empty key for all primitive types
1438  default:
1439  return empty_str;
1440  }
1441  }
1442 
1444  typename IteratorType::reference value() const
1445  {
1446  return anchor.value();
1447  }
1448  };
1449 
1451  typename IteratorType::reference container;
1452 
1453  public:
1455  explicit iteration_proxy(typename IteratorType::reference cont) noexcept
1456  : container(cont) {}
1457 
1459  iteration_proxy_internal begin() noexcept
1460  {
1461  return iteration_proxy_internal(container.begin());
1462  }
1463 
1465  iteration_proxy_internal end() noexcept
1466  {
1467  return iteration_proxy_internal(container.end());
1468  }
1469 };
1470 }
1471 }

1484 template<>
1485 struct external_constructor<value_t::boolean>
1486 {
1487  template<typename BasicJsonType>
1488  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t b) noexcept
1489  {
1490  j.m_type = value_t::boolean;
1491  j.m_value = b;
1492  j.assert_invariant();
1493  }
1494 };

1592 
1593  template<typename BasicJsonType>
1594  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const std::vector<bool>& arr)
1595  {
1596  j.m_type = value_t::array;
1597  j.m_value = value_t::array;
1598  j.m_value.array->reserve(arr.size());
1599  for (const bool x : arr)
1600  {
1601  j.m_value.array->push_back(x);
1602  }
1603  j.assert_invariant();
1604  }
1605 
1606  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T,
1607  enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<T, BasicJsonType>::value, int> = 0>
1608  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const std::valarray<T>& arr)
1609  {
1610  j.m_type = value_t::array;
1611  j.m_value = value_t::array;
1612  j.m_value.array->resize(arr.size());
1613  std::copy(std::begin(arr), std::end(arr), j.m_value.array->begin());
1614  j.assert_invariant();
1615  }
1616 };

1633  j.m_value = std::move(obj);
1634  j.assert_invariant();
1635  }

1638  enable_if_t<not std::is_same<CompatibleObjectType, typename BasicJsonType::object_t>::value, int> = 0>
1639  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const CompatibleObjectType& obj)
1640  {

1645  j.m_value.object = j.template create<typename BasicJsonType::object_t>(begin(obj), end(obj));
1646  j.assert_invariant();

1777 struct to_json_fn
1778 {
1779  private:
1780  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1781  auto call(BasicJsonType& j, T&& val, priority_tag<1> /*unused*/) const noexcept(noexcept(to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val))))
1782  -> decltype(to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val)), void())
1783  {
1784  return to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val));
1785  }
1786 
1787  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1788  void call(BasicJsonType& /*unused*/, T&& /*unused*/, priority_tag<0> /*unused*/) const noexcept
1789  {
1790  static_assert(sizeof(BasicJsonType) == 0,
1791  "could not find to_json() method in T's namespace");
1792 
1793 #ifdef _MSC_VER
1794  // MSVC does not show a stacktrace for the above assert
1795  using decayed = uncvref_t<T>;
1796  static_assert(sizeof(typename decayed::force_msvc_stacktrace) == 0,
1797  "forcing MSVC stacktrace to show which T we're talking about.");
1798 #endif
1799  }
1800 
1801  public:
1802  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1803  void operator()(BasicJsonType& j, T&& val) const
1804  noexcept(noexcept(std::declval<to_json_fn>().call(j, std::forward<T>(val), priority_tag<1> {})))
1805  {
1806  return call(j, std::forward<T>(val), priority_tag<1> {});
1807  }
1808 };
1809 }
1810

1813 {
1814 constexpr const auto& to_json = detail::static_const<detail::to_json_fn>::value;
1815 }

1857 struct input_adapter_protocol
1858 {
1860  virtual std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() = 0;
1861  virtual ~input_adapter_protocol() = default;
1862 };
1863 
1865 using input_adapter_t = std::shared_ptr<input_adapter_protocol>;
1866 
1876 class input_stream_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol
1877 {
1878  public:
1879  ~input_stream_adapter() override
1880  {
1881  // clear stream flags; we use underlying streambuf I/O, do not
1882  // maintain ifstream flags
1883  is.clear();
1884  }
1885 
1886  explicit input_stream_adapter(std::istream& i)
1887  : is(i), sb(*i.rdbuf())
1888  {}
1889 
1890  // delete because of pointer members
1891  input_stream_adapter(const input_stream_adapter&) = delete;
1892  input_stream_adapter& operator=(input_stream_adapter&) = delete;
1893 
1894  // std::istream/std::streambuf use std::char_traits<char>::to_int_type, to
1895  // ensure that std::char_traits<char>::eof() and the character 0xFF do not
1896  // end up as the same value, eg. 0xFFFFFFFF.
1897  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() override
1898  {
1899  return sb.sbumpc();
1900  }
1901 
1902  private:
1904  std::istream& is;
1905  std::streambuf& sb;
1906 };
1907 
1909 class input_buffer_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol
1910 {
1911  public:
1912  input_buffer_adapter(const char* b, const std::size_t l)
1913  : cursor(b), limit(b + l)
1914  {}
1915 
1916  // delete because of pointer members
1917  input_buffer_adapter(const input_buffer_adapter&) = delete;
1918  input_buffer_adapter& operator=(input_buffer_adapter&) = delete;
1919 
1920  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() noexcept override
1921  {
1922  if (JSON_LIKELY(cursor < limit))
1923  {
1924  return std::char_traits<char>::to_int_type(*(cursor++));
1925  }
1926 
1927  return std::char_traits<char>::eof();
1928  }
1929 
1930  private:
1932  const char* cursor;
1934  const char* const limit;
1935 };
1936 
1937 template<typename WideStringType>
1938 class wide_string_input_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol
1939 {
1940  public:
1941  explicit wide_string_input_adapter(const WideStringType& w) : str(w) {}
1942 
1943  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() noexcept override
1944  {
1945  // check if buffer needs to be filled
1946  if (utf8_bytes_index == utf8_bytes_filled)
1947  {
1948  if (sizeof(typename WideStringType::value_type) == 2)
1949  {
1950  fill_buffer_utf16();
1951  }
1952  else
1953  {
1954  fill_buffer_utf32();
1955  }
1956 
1957  assert(utf8_bytes_filled > 0);
1958  assert(utf8_bytes_index == 0);
1959  }
1960 
1961  // use buffer
1962  assert(utf8_bytes_filled > 0);
1963  assert(utf8_bytes_index < utf8_bytes_filled);
1964  return utf8_bytes[utf8_bytes_index++];
1965  }
1966 
1967  private:
1968  void fill_buffer_utf16()
1969  {
1970  utf8_bytes_index = 0;
1971 
1972  if (current_wchar == str.size())
1973  {
1974  utf8_bytes[0] = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
1975  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
1976  }
1977  else
1978  {
1979  // get the current character
1980  const int wc = static_cast<int>(str[current_wchar++]);
1981 
1982  // UTF-16 to UTF-8 encoding
1983  if (wc < 0x80)
1984  {
1985  utf8_bytes[0] = wc;
1986  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
1987  }
1988  else if (wc <= 0x7FF)
1989  {
1990  utf8_bytes[0] = 0xC0 | ((wc >> 6));
1991  utf8_bytes[1] = 0x80 | (wc & 0x3F);
1992  utf8_bytes_filled = 2;
1993  }
1994  else if (0xD800 > wc or wc >= 0xE000)
1995  {
1996  utf8_bytes[0] = 0xE0 | ((wc >> 12));
1997  utf8_bytes[1] = 0x80 | ((wc >> 6) & 0x3F);
1998  utf8_bytes[2] = 0x80 | (wc & 0x3F);
1999  utf8_bytes_filled = 3;
2000  }
2001  else
2002  {
2003  if (current_wchar < str.size())
2004  {
2005  const int wc2 = static_cast<int>(str[current_wchar++]);
2006  const int charcode = 0x10000 + (((wc & 0x3FF) << 10) | (wc2 & 0x3FF));
2007  utf8_bytes[0] = 0xf0 | (charcode >> 18);
2008  utf8_bytes[1] = 0x80 | ((charcode >> 12) & 0x3F);
2009  utf8_bytes[2] = 0x80 | ((charcode >> 6) & 0x3F);
2010  utf8_bytes[3] = 0x80 | (charcode & 0x3F);
2011  utf8_bytes_filled = 4;
2012  }
2013  else
2014  {
2015  // unknown character
2016  ++current_wchar;
2017  utf8_bytes[0] = wc;
2018  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
2019  }
2020  }
2021  }
2022  }
2023 
2024  void fill_buffer_utf32()
2025  {
2026  utf8_bytes_index = 0;
2027 
2028  if (current_wchar == str.size())
2029  {
2030  utf8_bytes[0] = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
2031  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
2032  }
2033  else
2034  {
2035  // get the current character
2036  const int wc = static_cast<int>(str[current_wchar++]);
2037 
2038  // UTF-32 to UTF-8 encoding
2039  if (wc < 0x80)
2040  {
2041  utf8_bytes[0] = wc;
2042  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
2043  }
2044  else if (wc <= 0x7FF)
2045  {
2046  utf8_bytes[0] = 0xC0 | ((wc >> 6) & 0x1F);
2047  utf8_bytes[1] = 0x80 | (wc & 0x3F);
2048  utf8_bytes_filled = 2;
2049  }
2050  else if (wc <= 0xFFFF)
2051  {
2052  utf8_bytes[0] = 0xE0 | ((wc >> 12) & 0x0F);
2053  utf8_bytes[1] = 0x80 | ((wc >> 6) & 0x3F);
2054  utf8_bytes[2] = 0x80 | (wc & 0x3F);
2055  utf8_bytes_filled = 3;
2056  }
2057  else if (wc <= 0x10FFFF)
2058  {
2059  utf8_bytes[0] = 0xF0 | ((wc >> 18 ) & 0x07);
2060  utf8_bytes[1] = 0x80 | ((wc >> 12) & 0x3F);
2061  utf8_bytes[2] = 0x80 | ((wc >> 6) & 0x3F);
2062  utf8_bytes[3] = 0x80 | (wc & 0x3F);
2063  utf8_bytes_filled = 4;
2064  }
2065  else
2066  {
2067  // unknown character
2068  utf8_bytes[0] = wc;
2069  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
2070  }
2071  }
2072  }
2073 
2074  private:
2076  const WideStringType& str;
2077 
2079  std::size_t current_wchar = 0;
2080 
2082  std::array<std::char_traits<char>::int_type, 4> utf8_bytes = {{0, 0, 0, 0}};
2083 
2085  std::size_t utf8_bytes_index = 0;
2087  std::size_t utf8_bytes_filled = 0;
2088 };

2090 class input_adapter
2091 {
2092  public:
2093  // native support
2094 
2096  input_adapter(std::istream& i)
2097  : ia(std::make_shared<input_stream_adapter>(i)) {}
2098 
2100  input_adapter(std::istream&& i)
2101  : ia(std::make_shared<input_stream_adapter>(i)) {}
2102

2104  : ia(std::make_shared<wide_string_input_adapter<std::wstring>>(ws)) {}
2105 
2106  input_adapter(const std::u16string& ws)
2107  : ia(std::make_shared<wide_string_input_adapter<std::u16string>>(ws)) {}
2108 
2109  input_adapter(const std::u32string& ws)
2110  : ia(std::make_shared<wide_string_input_adapter<std::u32string>>(ws)) {}
2111 
2113  template<typename CharT,
2114  typename std::enable_if<
2115  std::is_pointer<CharT>::value and
2116  std::is_integral<typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type>::value and
2117  sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type) == 1,
2118  int>::type = 0>
2119  input_adapter(CharT b, std::size_t l)
2120  : ia(std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b), l)) {}
2121 
2122  // derived support
2123 
2125  template<typename CharT,
2126  typename std::enable_if<
2127  std::is_pointer<CharT>::value and
2128  std::is_integral<typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type>::value and
2129  sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type) == 1,
2130  int>::type = 0>
2131  input_adapter(CharT b)
2132  : input_adapter(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b),
2133  std::strlen(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b))) {}
2134 
2136  template<class IteratorType,
2137  typename std::enable_if<
2138  std::is_same<typename std::iterator_traits<IteratorType>::iterator_category, std::random_access_iterator_tag>::value,
2139  int>::type = 0>
2140  input_adapter(IteratorType first, IteratorType last)
2141  {
2142  // assertion to check that the iterator range is indeed contiguous,
2143  // see http://stackoverflow.com/a/35008842/266378 for more discussion
2144  assert(std::accumulate(
2145  first, last, std::pair<bool, int>(true, 0),
2146  [&first](std::pair<bool, int> res, decltype(*first) val)
2147  {
2148  res.first &= (val == *(std::next(std::addressof(*first), res.second++)));
2149  return res;
2150  }).first);
2151 
2152  // assertion to check that each element is 1 byte long
2153  static_assert(
2154  sizeof(typename std::iterator_traits<IteratorType>::value_type) == 1,
2155  "each element in the iterator range must have the size of 1 byte");
2156 
2157  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(std::distance(first, last));
2158  if (JSON_LIKELY(len > 0))
2159  {
2160  // there is at least one element: use the address of first
2161  ia = std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(&(*first)), len);
2162  }
2163  else
2164  {
2165  // the address of first cannot be used: use nullptr
2166  ia = std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(nullptr, len);
2167  }
2168  }
2169 
2171  template<class T, std::size_t N>
2172  input_adapter(T (&array)[N])
2173  : input_adapter(std::begin(array), std::end(array)) {}
2174 
2176  template<class ContiguousContainer, typename
2177  std::enable_if<not std::is_pointer<ContiguousContainer>::value and
2178  std::is_base_of<std::random_access_iterator_tag, typename std::iterator_traits<decltype(std::begin(std::declval<ContiguousContainer const>()))>::iterator_category>::value,
2179  int>::type = 0>
2180  input_adapter(const ContiguousContainer& c)
2181  : input_adapter(std::begin(c), std::end(c)) {}
2182 
2183  operator input_adapter_t()
2184  {
2185  return ia;
2186  }
2187 
2188  private:
2190  input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
2191 };
2192 }

2224 template<typename BasicJsonType>
2225 class lexer
2226 {
2227  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
2228  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
2229  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
2230  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
2231 
2232  public:
2234  enum class token_type
2235  {
2236  uninitialized,
2237  literal_true,
2238  literal_false,
2239  literal_null,
2240  value_string,
2241  value_unsigned,
2242  value_integer,
2243  value_float,
2244  begin_array,
2245  begin_object,
2246  end_array,
2247  end_object,
2248  name_separator,
2249  value_separator,
2250  parse_error,
2251  end_of_input,
2252  literal_or_value
2253  };
2254 
2256  static const char* token_type_name(const token_type t) noexcept
2257  {
2258  switch (t)
2259  {
2260  case token_type::uninitialized:
2261  return "<uninitialized>";
2262  case token_type::literal_true:
2263  return "true literal";
2264  case token_type::literal_false:
2265  return "false literal";
2266  case token_type::literal_null:
2267  return "null literal";
2268  case token_type::value_string:
2269  return "string literal";
2270  case lexer::token_type::value_unsigned:
2271  case lexer::token_type::value_integer:
2272  case lexer::token_type::value_float:
2273  return "number literal";
2274  case token_type::begin_array:
2275  return "'['";
2276  case token_type::begin_object:
2277  return "'{'";
2278  case token_type::end_array:
2279  return "']'";
2280  case token_type::end_object:
2281  return "'}'";
2282  case token_type::name_separator:
2283  return "':'";
2284  case token_type::value_separator:
2285  return "','";
2286  case token_type::parse_error:
2287  return "<parse error>";
2288  case token_type::end_of_input:
2289  return "end of input";
2290  case token_type::literal_or_value:
2291  return "'[', '{', or a literal";
2292  default: // catch non-enum values
2293  return "unknown token"; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
2294  }
2295  }
2296 
2297  explicit lexer(detail::input_adapter_t&& adapter)
2298  : ia(std::move(adapter)), decimal_point_char(get_decimal_point()) {}
2299 
2300  // delete because of pointer members
2301  lexer(const lexer&) = delete;
2302  lexer& operator=(lexer&) = delete;
2303 
2304  private:
2306  // locales
2308 
2310  static char get_decimal_point() noexcept
2311  {
2312  const auto loc = localeconv();
2313  assert(loc != nullptr);
2314  return (loc->decimal_point == nullptr) ? '.' : *(loc->decimal_point);
2315  }
2316 
2318  // scan functions
2320 
2336  int get_codepoint()
2337  {
2338  // this function only makes sense after reading `\u`
2339  assert(current == 'u');
2340  int codepoint = 0;
2341 
2342  const auto factors = { 12, 8, 4, 0 };
2343  for (const auto factor : factors)
2344  {
2345  get();
2346 
2347  if (current >= '0' and current <= '9')
2348  {
2349  codepoint += ((current - 0x30) << factor);
2350  }
2351  else if (current >= 'A' and current <= 'F')
2352  {
2353  codepoint += ((current - 0x37) << factor);
2354  }
2355  else if (current >= 'a' and current <= 'f')
2356  {
2357  codepoint += ((current - 0x57) << factor);
2358  }
2359  else
2360  {
2361  return -1;
2362  }
2363  }
2364 
2365  assert(0x0000 <= codepoint and codepoint <= 0xFFFF);
2366  return codepoint;
2367  }
2368 
2384  bool next_byte_in_range(std::initializer_list<int> ranges)
2385  {
2386  assert(ranges.size() == 2 or ranges.size() == 4 or ranges.size() == 6);
2387  add(current);
2388 
2389  for (auto range = ranges.begin(); range != ranges.end(); ++range)
2390  {
2391  get();
2392  if (JSON_LIKELY(*range <= current and current <= *(++range)))
2393  {
2394  add(current);
2395  }
2396  else
2397  {
2398  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
2399  return false;
2400  }
2401  }
2402 
2403  return true;
2404  }
2405 
2421  token_type scan_string()
2422  {
2423  // reset token_buffer (ignore opening quote)
2424  reset();
2425 
2426  // we entered the function by reading an open quote
2427  assert(current == '\"');
2428 
2429  while (true)
2430  {
2431  // get next character
2432  switch (get())
2433  {
2434  // end of file while parsing string
2435  case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
2436  {
2437  error_message = "invalid string: missing closing quote";
2438  return token_type::parse_error;
2439  }
2440 
2441  // closing quote
2442  case '\"':
2443  {
2444  return token_type::value_string;
2445  }
2446 
2447  // escapes
2448  case '\\':
2449  {
2450  switch (get())
2451  {
2452  // quotation mark
2453  case '\"':
2454  add('\"');
2455  break;
2456  // reverse solidus
2457  case '\\':
2458  add('\\');
2459  break;
2460  // solidus
2461  case '/':
2462  add('/');
2463  break;
2464  // backspace
2465  case 'b':
2466  add('\b');
2467  break;
2468  // form feed
2469  case 'f':
2470  add('\f');
2471  break;
2472  // line feed
2473  case 'n':
2474  add('\n');
2475  break;
2476  // carriage return
2477  case 'r':
2478  add('\r');
2479  break;
2480  // tab
2481  case 't':
2482  add('\t');
2483  break;
2484 
2485  // unicode escapes
2486  case 'u':
2487  {
2488  const int codepoint1 = get_codepoint();
2489  int codepoint = codepoint1; // start with codepoint1
2490 
2491  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(codepoint1 == -1))
2492  {
2493  error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
2494  return token_type::parse_error;
2495  }
2496 
2497  // check if code point is a high surrogate
2498  if (0xD800 <= codepoint1 and codepoint1 <= 0xDBFF)
2499  {
2500  // expect next \uxxxx entry
2501  if (JSON_LIKELY(get() == '\\' and get() == 'u'))
2502  {
2503  const int codepoint2 = get_codepoint();
2504 
2505  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(codepoint2 == -1))
2506  {
2507  error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
2508  return token_type::parse_error;
2509  }
2510 
2511  // check if codepoint2 is a low surrogate
2512  if (JSON_LIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint2 and codepoint2 <= 0xDFFF))
2513  {
2514  // overwrite codepoint
2515  codepoint =
2516  // high surrogate occupies the most significant 22 bits
2517  (codepoint1 << 10)
2518  // low surrogate occupies the least significant 15 bits
2519  + codepoint2
2520  // there is still the 0xD800, 0xDC00 and 0x10000 noise
2521  // in the result so we have to subtract with:
2522  // (0xD800 << 10) + DC00 - 0x10000 = 0x35FDC00
2523  - 0x35FDC00;
2524  }
2525  else
2526  {
2527  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
2528  return token_type::parse_error;
2529  }
2530  }
2531  else
2532  {
2533  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
2534  return token_type::parse_error;
2535  }
2536  }
2537  else
2538  {
2539  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint1 and codepoint1 <= 0xDFFF))
2540  {
2541  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must follow U+D800..U+DBFF";
2542  return token_type::parse_error;
2543  }
2544  }
2545 
2546  // result of the above calculation yields a proper codepoint
2547  assert(0x00 <= codepoint and codepoint <= 0x10FFFF);
2548 
2549  // translate codepoint into bytes
2550  if (codepoint < 0x80)
2551  {
2552  // 1-byte characters: 0xxxxxxx (ASCII)
2553  add(codepoint);
2554  }
2555  else if (codepoint <= 0x7FF)
2556  {
2557  // 2-byte characters: 110xxxxx 10xxxxxx
2558  add(0xC0 | (codepoint >> 6));
2559  add(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F));
2560  }
2561  else if (codepoint <= 0xFFFF)
2562  {
2563  // 3-byte characters: 1110xxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
2564  add(0xE0 | (codepoint >> 12));
2565  add(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x3F));
2566  add(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F));
2567  }
2568  else
2569  {
2570  // 4-byte characters: 11110xxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
2571  add(0xF0 | (codepoint >> 18));
2572  add(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 12) & 0x3F));
2573  add(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x3F));
2574  add(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F));
2575  }
2576 
2577  break;
2578  }
2579 
2580  // other characters after escape
2581  default:
2582  error_message = "invalid string: forbidden character after backslash";
2583  return token_type::parse_error;
2584  }
2585 
2586  break;
2587  }
2588 
2589  // invalid control characters
2590  case 0x00:
2591  case 0x01:
2592  case 0x02:
2593  case 0x03:
2594  case 0x04:
2595  case 0x05:
2596  case 0x06:
2597  case 0x07:
2598  case 0x08:
2599  case 0x09:
2600  case 0x0A:
2601  case 0x0B:
2602  case 0x0C:
2603  case 0x0D:
2604  case 0x0E:
2605  case 0x0F:
2606  case 0x10:
2607  case 0x11:
2608  case 0x12:
2609  case 0x13:
2610  case 0x14:
2611  case 0x15:
2612  case 0x16:
2613  case 0x17:
2614  case 0x18:
2615  case 0x19:
2616  case 0x1A:
2617  case 0x1B:
2618  case 0x1C:
2619  case 0x1D:
2620  case 0x1E:
2621  case 0x1F:
2622  {
2623  error_message = "invalid string: control character must be escaped";
2624  return token_type::parse_error;
2625  }
2626 
2627  // U+0020..U+007F (except U+0022 (quote) and U+005C (backspace))
2628  case 0x20:
2629  case 0x21:
2630  case 0x23:
2631  case 0x24:
2632  case 0x25:
2633  case 0x26:
2634  case 0x27:
2635  case 0x28:
2636  case 0x29:
2637  case 0x2A:
2638  case 0x2B:
2639  case 0x2C:
2640  case 0x2D:
2641  case 0x2E:
2642  case 0x2F:
2643  case 0x30:
2644  case 0x31:
2645  case 0x32:
2646  case 0x33:
2647  case 0x34:
2648  case 0x35:
2649  case 0x36:
2650  case 0x37:
2651  case 0x38:
2652  case 0x39:
2653  case 0x3A:
2654  case 0x3B:
2655  case 0x3C:
2656  case 0x3D:
2657  case 0x3E:
2658  case 0x3F:
2659  case 0x40:
2660  case 0x41:
2661  case 0x42:
2662  case 0x43:
2663  case 0x44:
2664  case 0x45:
2665  case 0x46:
2666  case 0x47:
2667  case 0x48:
2668  case 0x49:
2669  case 0x4A:
2670  case 0x4B:
2671  case 0x4C:
2672  case 0x4D:
2673  case 0x4E:
2674  case 0x4F:
2675  case 0x50:
2676  case 0x51:
2677  case 0x52:
2678  case 0x53:
2679  case 0x54:
2680  case 0x55:
2681  case 0x56:
2682  case 0x57:
2683  case 0x58:
2684  case 0x59:
2685  case 0x5A:
2686  case 0x5B:
2687  case 0x5D:
2688  case 0x5E:
2689  case 0x5F:
2690  case 0x60:
2691  case 0x61:
2692  case 0x62:
2693  case 0x63:
2694  case 0x64:
2695  case 0x65:
2696  case 0x66:
2697  case 0x67:
2698  case 0x68:
2699  case 0x69:
2700  case 0x6A:
2701  case 0x6B:
2702  case 0x6C:
2703  case 0x6D:
2704  case 0x6E:
2705  case 0x6F:
2706  case 0x70:
2707  case 0x71:
2708  case 0x72:
2709  case 0x73:
2710  case 0x74:
2711  case 0x75:
2712  case 0x76:
2713  case 0x77:
2714  case 0x78:
2715  case 0x79:
2716  case 0x7A:
2717  case 0x7B:
2718  case 0x7C:
2719  case 0x7D:
2720  case 0x7E:
2721  case 0x7F:
2722  {
2723  add(current);
2724  break;
2725  }

2727  // U+0080..U+07FF: bytes C2..DF 80..BF
2728  case 0xC2:
2729  case 0xC3:
2730  case 0xC4:
2731  case 0xC5:
2732  case 0xC6:
2733  case 0xC7:
2734  case 0xC8:
2735  case 0xC9:
2736  case 0xCA:
2737  case 0xCB:
2738  case 0xCC:
2739  case 0xCD:
2740  case 0xCE:
2741  case 0xCF:
2742  case 0xD0:
2743  case 0xD1:
2744  case 0xD2:
2745  case 0xD3:
2746  case 0xD4:
2747  case 0xD5:
2748  case 0xD6:
2749  case 0xD7:
2750  case 0xD8:
2751  case 0xD9:

2767  case 0xE0:

2773  break;

2778  case 0xE1:

2794  {

2801  case 0xED:
2802  {

2804  {
2805  return token_type::parse_error;
2806  }
2807  break;
2808  }

2814  {
2815  return token_type::parse_error;
2816  }
2817  break;
2818  }

2820  // U+40000..U+FFFFF F1..F3 80..BF 80..BF 80..BF
2821  case 0xF1:
2822  case 0xF2:
2823  case 0xF3:
2824  {

2826  {
2827  return token_type::parse_error;
2828  }
2829  break;
2830  }

2836  {
2837  return token_type::parse_error;
2838  }
2839  break;

2841 
2842  // remaining bytes (80..C1 and F5..FF) are ill-formed
2843  default:
2844  {
2845  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
2846  return token_type::parse_error;
2847  }
2848  }
2849  }

2907  token_type scan_number()
2908  {
2909  // reset token_buffer to store the number's bytes
2910  reset();
2911 
2912  // the type of the parsed number; initially set to unsigned; will be
2913  // changed if minus sign, decimal point or exponent is read
2914  token_type number_type = token_type::value_unsigned;
2915 
2916  // state (init): we just found out we need to scan a number
2917  switch (current)
2918  {
2919  case '-':
2920  {
2921  add(current);
2922  goto scan_number_minus;
2923  }
2924 
2925  case '0':
2926  {
2927  add(current);
2928  goto scan_number_zero;
2929  }
2930 
2931  case '1':
2932  case '2':
2933  case '3':
2934  case '4':
2935  case '5':
2936  case '6':
2937  case '7':
2938  case '8':
2939  case '9':
2940  {
2941  add(current);
2942  goto scan_number_any1;
2943  }
2944 
2945  default:
2946  {
2947  // all other characters are rejected outside scan_number()
2948  assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
2949  }
2950  }
2951 
2952 scan_number_minus:
2953  // state: we just parsed a leading minus sign
2954  number_type = token_type::value_integer;
2955  switch (get())
2956  {
2957  case '0':
2958  {
2959  add(current);
2960  goto scan_number_zero;
2961  }
2962 
2963  case '1':
2964  case '2':
2965  case '3':
2966  case '4':
2967  case '5':
2968  case '6':
2969  case '7':
2970  case '8':
2971  case '9':
2972  {
2973  add(current);
2974  goto scan_number_any1;
2975  }
2976 
2977  default:
2978  {
2979  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '-'";
2980  return token_type::parse_error;
2981  }
2982  }
2983 
2984 scan_number_zero:
2985  // state: we just parse a zero (maybe with a leading minus sign)
2986  switch (get())
2987  {
2988  case '.':
2989  {
2990  add(decimal_point_char);
2991  goto scan_number_decimal1;
2992  }
2993 
2994  case 'e':
2995  case 'E':
2996  {
2997  add(current);
2998  goto scan_number_exponent;
2999  }
3000 
3001  default:
3002  goto scan_number_done;
3003  }
3004 
3005 scan_number_any1:
3006  // state: we just parsed a number 0-9 (maybe with a leading minus sign)
3007  switch (get())
3008  {
3009  case '0':
3010  case '1':
3011  case '2':
3012  case '3':
3013  case '4':
3014  case '5':
3015  case '6':
3016  case '7':
3017  case '8':
3018  case '9':
3019  {
3020  add(current);
3021  goto scan_number_any1;
3022  }
3023 
3024  case '.':
3025  {
3026  add(decimal_point_char);
3027  goto scan_number_decimal1;
3028  }
3029 
3030  case 'e':
3031  case 'E':
3032  {
3033  add(current);
3034  goto scan_number_exponent;
3035  }
3036 
3037  default:
3038  goto scan_number_done;
3039  }
3040 
3041 scan_number_decimal1:
3042  // state: we just parsed a decimal point
3043  number_type = token_type::value_float;
3044  switch (get())
3045  {
3046  case '0':
3047  case '1':
3048  case '2':
3049  case '3':
3050  case '4':
3051  case '5':
3052  case '6':
3053  case '7':
3054  case '8':
3055  case '9':
3056  {
3057  add(current);
3058  goto scan_number_decimal2;
3059  }
3060 
3061  default:
3062  {
3063  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '.'";
3064  return token_type::parse_error;
3065  }
3066  }
3067 
3068 scan_number_decimal2:
3069  // we just parsed at least one number after a decimal point
3070  switch (get())
3071  {
3072  case '0':
3073  case '1':
3074  case '2':
3075  case '3':
3076  case '4':
3077  case '5':
3078  case '6':
3079  case '7':
3080  case '8':
3081  case '9':
3082  {
3083  add(current);
3084  goto scan_number_decimal2;
3085  }
3086 
3087  case 'e':
3088  case 'E':
3089  {
3090  add(current);
3091  goto scan_number_exponent;
3092  }
3093 
3094  default:
3095  goto scan_number_done;
3096  }
3097 
3098 scan_number_exponent:
3099  // we just parsed an exponent
3100  number_type = token_type::value_float;
3101  switch (get())
3102  {
3103  case '+':
3104  case '-':
3105  {
3106  add(current);
3107  goto scan_number_sign;
3108  }
3109 
3110  case '0':
3111  case '1':
3112  case '2':
3113  case '3':
3114  case '4':
3115  case '5':
3116  case '6':
3117  case '7':
3118  case '8':
3119  case '9':
3120  {
3121  add(current);
3122  goto scan_number_any2;
3123  }
3124 
3125  default:
3126  {
3127  error_message =
3128  "invalid number; expected '+', '-', or digit after exponent";
3129  return token_type::parse_error;
3130  }
3131  }
3132 
3133 scan_number_sign:
3134  // we just parsed an exponent sign
3135  switch (get())
3136  {
3137  case '0':
3138  case '1':
3139  case '2':
3140  case '3':
3141  case '4':
3142  case '5':
3143  case '6':
3144  case '7':
3145  case '8':
3146  case '9':
3147  {
3148  add(current);
3149  goto scan_number_any2;
3150  }
3151 
3152  default:
3153  {
3154  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after exponent sign";
3155  return token_type::parse_error;
3156  }
3157  }
3158 
3159 scan_number_any2:
3160  // we just parsed a number after the exponent or exponent sign
3161  switch (get())
3162  {
3163  case '0':
3164  case '1':
3165  case '2':
3166  case '3':
3167  case '4':
3168  case '5':
3169  case '6':
3170  case '7':
3171  case '8':
3172  case '9':
3173  {
3174  add(current);
3175  goto scan_number_any2;
3176  }
3177 
3178  default:
3179  goto scan_number_done;
3180  }
3181 
3182 scan_number_done:
3183  // unget the character after the number (we only read it to know that
3184  // we are done scanning a number)
3185  unget();
3186 
3187  char* endptr = nullptr;
3188  errno = 0;
3189 
3190  // try to parse integers first and fall back to floats
3191  if (number_type == token_type::value_unsigned)
3192  {
3193  const auto x = std::strtoull(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
3194 
3195  // we checked the number format before
3196  assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
3197 
3198  if (errno == 0)
3199  {
3200  value_unsigned = static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(x);
3201  if (value_unsigned == x)
3202  {
3203  return token_type::value_unsigned;
3204  }
3205  }
3206  }
3207  else if (number_type == token_type::value_integer)
3208  {
3209  const auto x = std::strtoll(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
3210 
3211  // we checked the number format before
3212  assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
3213 
3214  if (errno == 0)
3215  {
3216  value_integer = static_cast<number_integer_t>(x);
3217  if (value_integer == x)
3218  {
3219  return token_type::value_integer;
3220  }
3221  }
3222  }
3223 
3224  // this code is reached if we parse a floating-point number or if an
3225  // integer conversion above failed
3226  strtof(value_float, token_buffer.data(), &endptr);
3227 
3228  // we checked the number format before
3229  assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
3230 
3231  return token_type::value_float;
3232  }
3233 
3239  token_type scan_literal(const char* literal_text, const std::size_t length,
3240  token_type return_type)
3241  {
3242  assert(current == literal_text[0]);
3243  for (std::size_t i = 1; i < length; ++i)
3244  {
3245  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(get() != literal_text[i]))
3246  {
3247  error_message = "invalid literal";
3248  return token_type::parse_error;
3249  }
3250  }
3251  return return_type;
3252  }
3253 
3255  // input management
3257 
3259  void reset() noexcept
3260  {
3261  token_buffer.clear();
3262  token_string.clear();
3263  token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(current));
3264  }
3265 
3266  /*
3267  @brief get next character from the input
3268 
3269  This function provides the interface to the used input adapter. It does
3270  not throw in case the input reached EOF, but returns a
3271  `std::char_traits<char>::eof()` in that case. Stores the scanned characters
3272  for use in error messages.
3273 
3274  @return character read from the input
3275  */
3276  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get()
3277  {
3278  ++chars_read;
3279  if (next_unget)
3280  {
3281  // just reset the next_unget variable and work with current
3282  next_unget = false;
3283  }
3284  else
3285  {
3286  current = ia->get_character();
3287  }
3288 
3289  if (JSON_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof()))
3290  {
3291  token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(current));
3292  }
3293  return current;
3294  }
3295 
3304  void unget()
3305  {
3306  next_unget = true;
3307  --chars_read;
3308  if (JSON_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof()))
3309  {
3310  assert(token_string.size() != 0);
3311  token_string.pop_back();
3312  }
3313  }
3314 
3316  void add(int c)
3317  {
3318  token_buffer.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(c));
3319  }
3320 
3321  public:
3323  // value getters
3325 
3327  constexpr number_integer_t get_number_integer() const noexcept
3328  {
3329  return value_integer;
3330  }
3331 
3333  constexpr number_unsigned_t get_number_unsigned() const noexcept
3334  {
3335  return value_unsigned;
3336  }
3337 
3339  constexpr number_float_t get_number_float() const noexcept
3340  {
3341  return value_float;
3342  }
3343 
3345  string_t& get_string()
3346  {
3347  return token_buffer;
3348  }
3349 
3351  // diagnostics
3353 
3355  constexpr std::size_t get_position() const noexcept
3356  {
3357  return chars_read;
3358  }
3359 
3363  std::string get_token_string() const
3364  {
3365  // escape control characters
3366  std::string result;
3367  for (const auto c : token_string)
3368  {
3369  if ('\x00' <= c and c <= '\x1F')
3370  {
3371  // escape control characters
3372  char cs[9];
3373  snprintf(cs, 9, "<U+%.4X>", static_cast<unsigned char>(c));
3374  result += cs;
3375  }
3376  else
3377  {
3378  // add character as is
3379  result.push_back(c);
3380  }
3381  }
3382 
3383  return result;
3384  }
3385 
3387  constexpr const char* get_error_message() const noexcept
3388  {
3389  return error_message;
3390  }
3391 
3393  // actual scanner
3395 
3400  bool skip_bom()
3401  {
3402  if (get() == 0xEF)
3403  {
3404  if (get() == 0xBB and get() == 0xBF)
3405  {
3406  // we completely parsed the BOM
3407  return true;
3408  }
3409  else
3410  {
3411  // after reading 0xEF, an unexpected character followed
3412  return false;
3413  }
3414  }
3415  else
3416  {
3417  // the first character is not the beginning of the BOM; unget it to
3418  // process is later
3419  unget();
3420  return true;
3421  }
3422  }
3423 
3424  token_type scan()
3425  {
3426  // initially, skip the BOM
3427  if (chars_read == 0 and not skip_bom())
3428  {
3429  error_message = "invalid BOM; must be 0xEF 0xBB 0xBF if given";
3430  return token_type::parse_error;
3431  }
3432 
3433  // read next character and ignore whitespace
3434  do
3435  {
3436  get();
3437  }
3438  while (current == ' ' or current == '\t' or current == '\n' or current == '\r');
3439 
3440  switch (current)
3441  {
3442  // structural characters
3443  case '[':
3444  return token_type::begin_array;
3445  case ']':
3446  return token_type::end_array;
3447  case '{':
3448  return token_type::begin_object;
3449  case '}':
3450  return token_type::end_object;
3451  case ':':
3452  return token_type::name_separator;
3453  case ',':
3454  return token_type::value_separator;
3455 
3456  // literals
3457  case 't':
3458  return scan_literal("true", 4, token_type::literal_true);
3459  case 'f':
3460  return scan_literal("false", 5, token_type::literal_false);
3461  case 'n':
3462  return scan_literal("null", 4, token_type::literal_null);
3463 
3464  // string
3465  case '\"':
3466  return scan_string();
3467 
3468  // number
3469  case '-':
3470  case '0':
3471  case '1':
3472  case '2':
3473  case '3':
3474  case '4':
3475  case '5':
3476  case '6':
3477  case '7':
3478  case '8':
3479  case '9':
3480  return scan_number();
3481 
3482  // end of input (the null byte is needed when parsing from
3483  // string literals)
3484  case '\0':
3485  case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
3486  return token_type::end_of_input;
3487 
3488  // error
3489  default:
3490  error_message = "invalid literal";
3491  return token_type::parse_error;
3492  }
3493  }
3494 
3495  private:
3497  detail::input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
3498 
3500  std::char_traits<char>::int_type current = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
3501 
3503  bool next_unget = false;
3504 
3506  std::size_t chars_read = 0;
3507 
3509  std::vector<char> token_string {};
3510 
3512  string_t token_buffer {};
3513 
3515  const char* error_message = "";
3516 
3517  // number values
3518  number_integer_t value_integer = 0;
3519  number_unsigned_t value_unsigned = 0;
3520  number_float_t value_float = 0;
3521 
3523  const char decimal_point_char = '.';
3524 };
3525 }
3526 }

3562 template<typename BasicJsonType>
3563 struct json_sax
3564 {
3566  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
3568  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
3570  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
3572  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
3573 
3575  static constexpr auto no_limit = std::size_t(-1);
3576 
3581  virtual bool null() = 0;
3582 
3588  virtual bool boolean(bool val) = 0;
3589 
3595  virtual bool number_integer(number_integer_t val) = 0;
3596 
3602  virtual bool number_unsigned(number_unsigned_t val) = 0;
3603 
3610  virtual bool number_float(number_float_t val, const string_t& s) = 0;
3611 
3617  virtual bool string(string_t& val) = 0;
3618 
3625  virtual bool start_object(std::size_t elements = no_limit) = 0;
3626 
3632  virtual bool key(string_t& val) = 0;
3633 
3638  virtual bool end_object() = 0;
3639 
3646  virtual bool start_array(std::size_t elements = no_limit) = 0;
3647 
3652  virtual bool end_array() = 0;
3653 
3661  virtual bool parse_error(std::size_t position,
3662  const std::string& last_token,
3663  const detail::exception& ex) = 0;
3664 
3665  virtual ~json_sax() = default;
3666 };

3692 
3698  json_sax_dom_parser(BasicJsonType& r, const bool allow_exceptions_ = true)
3699  : root(r), allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_)
3700  {}
3701 
3702  bool null() override
3703  {
3704  handle_value(nullptr);
3705  return true;
3706  }
3707

3709  {
3710  handle_value(val);
3711  return true;
3712  }

3739  {
3740  ref_stack.push_back(handle_value(BasicJsonType::value_t::object));
3741 
3742  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(len != json_sax<BasicJsonType>::no_limit and len > ref_stack.back()->max_size()))
3743  {
3744  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408,
3745  "excessive object size: " + std::to_string(len)));

3769  {

3783  bool parse_error(std::size_t, const std::string&,
3784  const detail::exception& ex) override
3785  {
3786  errored = true;
3787  if (allow_exceptions)
3788  {
3789  // determine the proper exception type from the id
3790  switch ((ex.id / 100) % 100)
3791  {
3792  case 1:
3793  JSON_THROW(*reinterpret_cast<const detail::parse_error*>(&ex));
3794  case 2:
3795  JSON_THROW(*reinterpret_cast<const detail::invalid_iterator*>(&ex)); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
3796  case 3:
3797  JSON_THROW(*reinterpret_cast<const detail::type_error*>(&ex)); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
3798  case 4:
3799  JSON_THROW(*reinterpret_cast<const detail::out_of_range*>(&ex));
3800  case 5:
3801  JSON_THROW(*reinterpret_cast<const detail::other_error*>(&ex)); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
3802  default:
3803  assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
3804  }
3805  }
3806  return false;
3807  }
3808 
3809  constexpr bool is_errored() const
3810  {
3811  return errored;
3812  }
3813 
3814  private:
3821  template<typename Value>
3822  BasicJsonType* handle_value(Value&& v)
3823  {
3824  if (ref_stack.empty())
3825  {
3826  root = BasicJsonType(std::forward<Value>(v));
3827  return &root;
3828  }
3829  else
3830  {
3831  assert(ref_stack.back()->is_array() or ref_stack.back()->is_object());
3832  if (ref_stack.back()->is_array())
3833  {
3834  ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->emplace_back(std::forward<Value>(v));
3835  return &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->back());
3836  }
3837  else
3838  {
3839  assert(object_element);
3840  *object_element = BasicJsonType(std::forward<Value>(v));
3841  return object_element;
3842  }
3843  }
3844  }
3845 
3847  BasicJsonType& root;
3849  std::vector<BasicJsonType*> ref_stack;
3851  BasicJsonType* object_element = nullptr;
3853  bool errored = false;
3855  const bool allow_exceptions = true;
3856 };

3858 template<typename BasicJsonType>
3859 class json_sax_dom_callback_parser : public json_sax<BasicJsonType>
3860 {
3861  public:
3862  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
3863  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
3864  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
3865  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
3866  using parser_callback_t = typename BasicJsonType::parser_callback_t;
3867  using parse_event_t = typename BasicJsonType::parse_event_t;
3868 
3869  json_sax_dom_callback_parser(BasicJsonType& r,
3870  const parser_callback_t cb,
3871  const bool allow_exceptions_ = true)
3872  : root(r), callback(cb), allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_)
3873  {
3874  keep_stack.push_back(true);
3875  }
3876 
3877  bool null() override
3878  {
3879  handle_value(nullptr);
3880  return true;
3881  }
3882 
3883  bool boolean(bool val) override
3884  {
3885  handle_value(val);
3886  return true;
3887  }
3888 
3889  bool number_integer(number_integer_t val) override
3890  {
3891  handle_value(val);
3892  return true;
3893  }
3894 
3895  bool number_unsigned(number_unsigned_t val) override
3896  {
3897  handle_value(val);
3898  return true;
3899  }
3900 
3901  bool number_float(number_float_t val, const string_t&) override
3902  {
3903  handle_value(val);
3904  return true;
3905  }
3906 
3907  bool string(string_t& val) override
3908  {
3909  handle_value(val);
3910  return true;
3911  }
3912 
3913  bool start_object(std::size_t len) override
3914  {
3915  // check callback for object start
3916  const bool keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::object_start, discarded);
3917  keep_stack.push_back(keep);
3918 
3919  auto val = handle_value(BasicJsonType::value_t::object, true);
3920  ref_stack.push_back(val.second);
3921 
3922  // check object limit
3923  if (ref_stack.back())
3924  {
3925  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(len != json_sax<BasicJsonType>::no_limit and len > ref_stack.back()->max_size()))
3926  {
3927  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408,
3928  "excessive object size: " + std::to_string(len)));
3929  }
3930  }
3931 
3932  return true;
3933  }
3934 
3935  bool key(string_t& val) override
3936  {
3937  BasicJsonType k = BasicJsonType(val);
3938 
3939  // check callback for key
3940  const bool keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::key, k);
3941  key_keep_stack.push_back(keep);
3942 
3943  // add discarded value at given key and store the reference for later
3944  if (keep and ref_stack.back())
3945  {
3946  object_element = &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.object->operator[](val) = discarded);
3947  }
3948 
3949  return true;
3950  }
3951 
3952  bool end_object() override
3953  {
3954  if (ref_stack.back())
3955  {
3956  if (not callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()) - 1, parse_event_t::object_end, *ref_stack.back()))
3957  {
3958  // discard object
3959  *ref_stack.back() = discarded;
3960  }
3961  }
3962 
3963  assert(not ref_stack.empty());
3964  assert(not keep_stack.empty());
3965  ref_stack.pop_back();
3966  keep_stack.pop_back();
3967 
3968  if (not ref_stack.empty() and ref_stack.back())
3969  {
3970  // remove discarded value
3971  if (ref_stack.back()->is_object())
3972  {
3973  for (auto it = ref_stack.back()->begin(); it != ref_stack.back()->end(); ++it)
3974  {
3975  if (it->is_discarded())
3976  {
3977  ref_stack.back()->erase(it);
3978  break;
3979  }
3980  }
3981  }
3982  }
3983 
3984  return true;
3985  }
3986 
3987  bool start_array(std::size_t len) override
3988  {
3989  const bool keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::array_start, discarded);
3990  keep_stack.push_back(keep);
3991 
3992  auto val = handle_value(BasicJsonType::value_t::array, true);
3993  ref_stack.push_back(val.second);
3994 
3995  // check array limit
3996  if (ref_stack.back())
3997  {
3998  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(len != json_sax<BasicJsonType>::no_limit and len > ref_stack.back()->max_size()))
3999  {
4000  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408,
4001  "excessive array size: " + std::to_string(len)));
4002  }
4003  }
4004 
4005  return true;
4006  }
4007 
4008  bool end_array() override
4009  {
4010  bool keep = true;
4011 
4012  if (ref_stack.back())
4013  {
4014  keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()) - 1, parse_event_t::array_end, *ref_stack.back());
4015  if (not keep)
4016  {
4017  // discard array
4018  *ref_stack.back() = discarded;
4019  }
4020  }
4021 
4022  assert(not ref_stack.empty());
4023  assert(not keep_stack.empty());
4024  ref_stack.pop_back();
4025  keep_stack.pop_back();
4026 
4027  // remove discarded value
4028  if (not keep and not ref_stack.empty())
4029  {
4030  if (ref_stack.back()->is_array())
4031  {
4032  ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->pop_back();
4033  }
4034  }
4035 
4036  return true;
4037  }
4038 
4039  bool parse_error(std::size_t, const std::string&,
4040  const detail::exception& ex) override
4041  {
4042  errored = true;
4043  if (allow_exceptions)
4044  {
4045  // determine the proper exception type from the id
4046  switch ((ex.id / 100) % 100)
4047  {
4048  case 1:
4049  JSON_THROW(*reinterpret_cast<const detail::parse_error*>(&ex));
4050  case 2:
4051  JSON_THROW(*reinterpret_cast<const detail::invalid_iterator*>(&ex)); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
4052  case 3:
4053  JSON_THROW(*reinterpret_cast<const detail::type_error*>(&ex)); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
4054  case 4:
4055  JSON_THROW(*reinterpret_cast<const detail::out_of_range*>(&ex));
4056  case 5:
4057  JSON_THROW(*reinterpret_cast<const detail::other_error*>(&ex)); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
4058  default:
4059  assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
4060  }
4061  }
4062  return false;
4063  }
4064 
4065  constexpr bool is_errored() const
4066  {
4067  return errored;
4068  }
4069 
4070  private:
4086  template<typename Value>
4087  std::pair<bool, BasicJsonType*> handle_value(Value&& v, const bool skip_callback = false)
4088  {
4089  assert(not keep_stack.empty());
4090 
4091  // do not handle this value if we know it would be added to a discarded
4092  // container
4093  if (not keep_stack.back())
4094  {
4095  return {false, nullptr};
4096  }
4097 
4098  // create value
4099  auto value = BasicJsonType(std::forward<Value>(v));
4100 
4101  // check callback
4102  const bool keep = skip_callback or callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::value, value);
4103 
4104  // do not handle this value if we just learnt it shall be discarded
4105  if (not keep)
4106  {
4107  return {false, nullptr};
4108  }
4109 
4110  if (ref_stack.empty())
4111  {
4112  root = std::move(value);
4113  return {true, &root};
4114  }
4115  else
4116  {
4117  assert(ref_stack.back()->is_array() or ref_stack.back()->is_object());
4118  if (ref_stack.back()->is_array())
4119  {
4120  ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->push_back(std::move(value));
4121  return {true, &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->back())};
4122  }
4123  else
4124  {
4125  // check if we should store an element for the current key
4126  assert(not key_keep_stack.empty());
4127  const bool store_element = key_keep_stack.back();
4128  key_keep_stack.pop_back();
4129 
4130  if (not store_element)
4131  {
4132  return {false, nullptr};
4133  }
4134 
4135  assert(object_element);
4136  *object_element = std::move(value);
4137  return {true, object_element};
4138  }
4139  }
4140  }
4141 
4143  BasicJsonType& root;
4145  std::vector<BasicJsonType*> ref_stack;
4147  std::vector<bool> keep_stack;
4149  std::vector<bool> key_keep_stack;
4151  BasicJsonType* object_element = nullptr;
4153  bool errored = false;
4155  const parser_callback_t callback = nullptr;
4157  const bool allow_exceptions = true;
4159  BasicJsonType discarded = BasicJsonType::value_t::discarded;
4160 };
4161 
4162 template<typename BasicJsonType>
4163 class json_sax_acceptor : public json_sax<BasicJsonType>
4164 {
4165  public:
4166  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
4167  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
4168  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
4169  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
4170 
4171  bool null() override
4172  {
4173  return true;
4174  }
4175 
4176  bool boolean(bool) override
4177  {
4178  return true;
4179  }
4180 
4181  bool number_integer(number_integer_t) override
4182  {
4183  return true;
4184  }
4185 
4186  bool number_unsigned(number_unsigned_t) override
4187  {
4188  return true;
4189  }
4190 
4191  bool number_float(number_float_t, const string_t&) override
4192  {
4193  return true;
4194  }
4195 
4196  bool string(string_t&) override
4197  {
4198  return true;
4199  }
4200 
4201  bool start_object(std::size_t) override
4202  {
4203  return true;
4204  }
4205 
4206  bool key(string_t&) override
4207  {
4208  return true;
4209  }
4210

4212  {
4213  return true;
4214  }
4215

4217  {
4218  return true;
4219  }
4220 
4221  bool end_array() override
4222  {
4223  return true;
4224  }
4225

4227  {

4230 };
4231 }
