4235 // #include <nlohmann/detail/input/lexer.hpp>
4236 
4237 // #include <nlohmann/detail/value_t.hpp>
4238 
4239 
4240 namespace nlohmann
4241 {
4242 namespace detail
4243 {
4245 // parser //
4247 
4253 template<typename BasicJsonType>
4254 class parser
4255 {
4256  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
4257  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
4258  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
4259  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
4260  using lexer_t = lexer<BasicJsonType>;
4261  using token_type = typename lexer_t::token_type;
4262 
4263  public:
4264  enum class parse_event_t : uint8_t
4265  {
4267  object_start,
4269  object_end,
4271  array_start,
4273  array_end,
4275  key,
4277  value
4278  };
4279 
4280  using json_sax_t = json_sax<BasicJsonType>;
4281 
4282  using parser_callback_t =
4283  std::function<bool(int depth, parse_event_t event, BasicJsonType& parsed)>;
4284 
4286  explicit parser(detail::input_adapter_t&& adapter,
4287  const parser_callback_t cb = nullptr,
4288  const bool allow_exceptions_ = true)
4289  : callback(cb), m_lexer(std::move(adapter)), allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_)
4290  {
4291  // read first token
4292  get_token();
4293  }
4294 
4305  void parse(const bool strict, BasicJsonType& result)
4306  {
4307  if (callback)
4308  {
4309  json_sax_dom_callback_parser<BasicJsonType> sdp(result, callback, allow_exceptions);
4310  sax_parse_internal(&sdp);
4311  result.assert_invariant();
4312 
4313  // in strict mode, input must be completely read
4314  if (strict and (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input))
4315  {
4316  sdp.parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
4317  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
4318  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::end_of_input)));
4319  }
4320 
4321  // in case of an error, return discarded value
4322  if (sdp.is_errored())
4323  {
4324  result = value_t::discarded;
4325  return;
4326  }
4327 
4328  // set top-level value to null if it was discarded by the callback
4329  // function
4330  if (result.is_discarded())
4331  {
4332  result = nullptr;
4333  }
4334  }
4335  else
4336  {
4337  json_sax_dom_parser<BasicJsonType> sdp(result, allow_exceptions);
4338  sax_parse_internal(&sdp);
4339  result.assert_invariant();
4340 
4341  // in strict mode, input must be completely read
4342  if (strict and (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input))
4343  {
4344  sdp.parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
4345  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
4346  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::end_of_input)));
4347  }
4348 
4349  // in case of an error, return discarded value
4350  if (sdp.is_errored())
4351  {
4352  result = value_t::discarded;
4353  return;
4354  }
4355  }
4356  }
4357 
4364  bool accept(const bool strict = true)
4365  {
4366  json_sax_acceptor<BasicJsonType> sax_acceptor;
4367  return sax_parse(&sax_acceptor, strict);
4368  }
4369 
4370  bool sax_parse(json_sax_t* sax, const bool strict = true)
4371  {
4372  const bool result = sax_parse_internal(sax);
4373 
4374  // strict mode: next byte must be EOF
4375  if (result and strict and (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input))
4376  {
4377  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
4378  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
4379  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::end_of_input)));
4380  }
4381 
4382  return result;
4383  }
4384 
4385  private:
4386  bool sax_parse_internal(json_sax_t* sax)
4387  {
4388  // stack to remember the hieararchy of structured values we are parsing
4389  // true = array; false = object
4390  std::vector<bool> states;
4391  // value to avoid a goto (see comment where set to true)
4392  bool skip_to_state_evaluation = false;
4393 
4394  while (true)
4395  {
4396  if (not skip_to_state_evaluation)
4397  {
4398  // invariant: get_token() was called before each iteration
4399  switch (last_token)
4400  {
4401  case token_type::begin_object:
4402  {
4403  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object()))
4404  {
4405  return false;
4406  }
4407 
4408  // closing } -> we are done
4409  if (get_token() == token_type::end_object)
4410  {
4411  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->end_object()))
4412  {
4413  return false;
4414  }
4415  break;
4416  }
4417 
4418  // parse key
4419  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(last_token != token_type::value_string))
4420  {
4421  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
4422  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
4423  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::value_string)));
4424  }
4425  else
4426  {
4427  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->key(m_lexer.get_string())))
4428  {
4429  return false;
4430  }
4431  }
4432 
4433  // parse separator (:)
4434  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::name_separator))
4435  {
4436  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
4437  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
4438  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::name_separator)));
4439  }
4440 
4441  // remember we are now inside an object
4442  states.push_back(false);
4443 
4444  // parse values
4445  get_token();
4446  continue;
4447  }
4448 
4449  case token_type::begin_array:
4450  {
4451  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array()))
4452  {
4453  return false;
4454  }
4455 
4456  // closing ] -> we are done
4457  if (get_token() == token_type::end_array)
4458  {
4459  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->end_array()))
4460  {
4461  return false;
4462  }
4463  break;
4464  }
4465 
4466  // remember we are now inside an array
4467  states.push_back(true);
4468 
4469  // parse values (no need to call get_token)
4470  continue;
4471  }
4472 
4473  case token_type::value_float:
4474  {
4475  const auto res = m_lexer.get_number_float();
4476 
4477  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not std::isfinite(res)))
4478  {
4479  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
4480  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
4481  out_of_range::create(406, "number overflow parsing '" + m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'"));
4482  }
4483  else
4484  {
4485  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->number_float(res, m_lexer.get_string())))
4486  {
4487  return false;
4488  }
4489  break;
4490  }
4491  }
4492 
4493  case token_type::literal_false:
4494  {
4495  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->boolean(false)))
4496  {
4497  return false;
4498  }
4499  break;
4500  }
4501 
4502  case token_type::literal_null:
4503  {
4504  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->null()))
4505  {
4506  return false;
4507  }
4508  break;
4509  }
4510 
4511  case token_type::literal_true:
4512  {
4513  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->boolean(true)))
4514  {
4515  return false;
4516  }
4517  break;
4518  }
4519 
4520  case token_type::value_integer:
4521  {
4522  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->number_integer(m_lexer.get_number_integer())))
4523  {
4524  return false;
4525  }
4526  break;
4527  }
4528 
4529  case token_type::value_string:
4530  {
4531  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->string(m_lexer.get_string())))
4532  {
4533  return false;
4534  }
4535  break;
4536  }
4537 
4538  case token_type::value_unsigned:
4539  {
4540  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->number_unsigned(m_lexer.get_number_unsigned())))
4541  {
4542  return false;
4543  }
4544  break;
4545  }
4546 
4547  case token_type::parse_error:
4548  {
4549  // using "uninitialized" to avoid "expected" message
4550  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
4551  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
4552  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::uninitialized)));
4553  }
4554 
4555  default: // the last token was unexpected
4556  {
4557  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
4558  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
4559  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::literal_or_value)));
4560  }
4561  }
4562  }
4563  else
4564  {
4565  skip_to_state_evaluation = false;
4566  }
4567 
4568  // we reached this line after we successfully parsed a value
4569  if (states.empty())
4570  {
4571  // empty stack: we reached the end of the hieararchy: done
4572  return true;
4573  }
4574  else
4575  {
4576  if (states.back()) // array
4577  {
4578  // comma -> next value
4579  if (get_token() == token_type::value_separator)
4580  {
4581  // parse a new value
4582  get_token();
4583  continue;
4584  }
4585 
4586  // closing ]
4587  if (JSON_LIKELY(last_token == token_type::end_array))
4588  {
4589  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->end_array()))
4590  {
4591  return false;
4592  }
4593 
4594  // We are done with this array. Before we can parse a
4595  // new value, we need to evaluate the new state first.
4596  // By setting skip_to_state_evaluation to false, we
4597  // are effectively jumping to the beginning of this if.
4598  assert(not states.empty());
4599  states.pop_back();
4600  skip_to_state_evaluation = true;
4601  continue;
4602  }
4603  else
4604  {
4605  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
4606  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
4607  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::end_array)));
4608  }
4609  }
4610  else // object
4611  {
4612  // comma -> next value
4613  if (get_token() == token_type::value_separator)
4614  {
4615  // parse key
4616  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::value_string))
4617  {
4618  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
4619  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
4620  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::value_string)));
4621  }
4622  else
4623  {
4624  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->key(m_lexer.get_string())))
4625  {
4626  return false;
4627  }
4628  }
4629 
4630  // parse separator (:)
4631  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::name_separator))
4632  {
4633  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
4634  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
4635  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::name_separator)));
4636  }
4637 
4638  // parse values
4639  get_token();
4640  continue;
4641  }
4642 
4643  // closing }
4644  if (JSON_LIKELY(last_token == token_type::end_object))
4645  {
4646  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->end_object()))
4647  {
4648  return false;
4649  }
4650 
4651  // We are done with this object. Before we can parse a
4652  // new value, we need to evaluate the new state first.
4653  // By setting skip_to_state_evaluation to false, we
4654  // are effectively jumping to the beginning of this if.
4655  assert(not states.empty());
4656  states.pop_back();
4657  skip_to_state_evaluation = true;
4658  continue;
4659  }
4660  else
4661  {
4662  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
4663  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
4664  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::end_object)));
4665  }
4666  }
4667  }
4668  }
4669  }
4670 
4672  token_type get_token()
4673  {
4674  return (last_token = m_lexer.scan());
4675  }
4676 
4677  std::string exception_message(const token_type expected)
4678  {
4679  std::string error_msg = "syntax error - ";
4680  if (last_token == token_type::parse_error)
4681  {
4682  error_msg += std::string(m_lexer.get_error_message()) + "; last read: '" +
4683  m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'";
4684  }
4685  else
4686  {
4687  error_msg += "unexpected " + std::string(lexer_t::token_type_name(last_token));
4688  }
4689 
4690  if (expected != token_type::uninitialized)
4691  {
4692  error_msg += "; expected " + std::string(lexer_t::token_type_name(expected));
4693  }
4694 
4695  return error_msg;
4696  }
4697 
4698  private:
4700  const parser_callback_t callback = nullptr;
4702  token_type last_token = token_type::uninitialized;
4704  lexer_t m_lexer;
4706  const bool allow_exceptions = true;
4707 };
4708 }
4709 }
4710 
4711 // #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/primitive_iterator.hpp>
4712 
4713 
4714 #include <cstddef> // ptrdiff_t
4715 #include <limits> // numeric_limits
4716 
4717 namespace nlohmann
4718 {
4719 namespace detail
4720 {
4721 /*
4722 @brief an iterator for primitive JSON types
4723 
4724 This class models an iterator for primitive JSON types (boolean, number,
4725 string). It's only purpose is to allow the iterator/const_iterator classes
4726 to "iterate" over primitive values. Internally, the iterator is modeled by
4727 a `difference_type` variable. Value begin_value (`0`) models the begin,
4728 end_value (`1`) models past the end.
4729 */
4730 class primitive_iterator_t
4731 {
4732  private:
4733  using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
4734  static constexpr difference_type begin_value = 0;
4735  static constexpr difference_type end_value = begin_value + 1;
4736 
4738  difference_type m_it = (std::numeric_limits<std::ptrdiff_t>::min)();
4739 
4740  public:
4741  constexpr difference_type get_value() const noexcept
4742  {
4743  return m_it;
4744  }
4745 
4747  void set_begin() noexcept
4748  {
4749  m_it = begin_value;
4750  }
4751 
4753  void set_end() noexcept
4754  {
4755  m_it = end_value;
4756  }
4757 
4759  constexpr bool is_begin() const noexcept
4760  {
4761  return m_it == begin_value;
4762  }
4763 
4765  constexpr bool is_end() const noexcept
4766  {
4767  return m_it == end_value;
4768  }
4769 
4770  friend constexpr bool operator==(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
4771  {
4772  return lhs.m_it == rhs.m_it;
4773  }
4774 
4775  friend constexpr bool operator<(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
4776  {
4777  return lhs.m_it < rhs.m_it;
4778  }
4779 
4780  primitive_iterator_t operator+(difference_type n) noexcept
4781  {
4782  auto result = *this;
4783  result += n;
4784  return result;
4785  }
4786 
4787  friend constexpr difference_type operator-(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
4788  {
4789  return lhs.m_it - rhs.m_it;
4790  }
4791 
4792  primitive_iterator_t& operator++() noexcept
4793  {
4794  ++m_it;
4795  return *this;
4796  }
4797 
4798  primitive_iterator_t const operator++(int) noexcept
4799  {
4800  auto result = *this;
4801  ++m_it;
4802  return result;
4803  }
4804 
4805  primitive_iterator_t& operator--() noexcept
4806  {
4807  --m_it;
4808  return *this;
4809  }
4810 
4811  primitive_iterator_t const operator--(int) noexcept
4812  {
4813  auto result = *this;
4814  --m_it;
4815  return result;
4816  }
4817 
4818  primitive_iterator_t& operator+=(difference_type n) noexcept
4819  {
4820  m_it += n;
4821  return *this;
4822  }
4823 
4824  primitive_iterator_t& operator-=(difference_type n) noexcept
4825  {
4826  m_it -= n;
4827  return *this;
4828  }
4829 };
4830 }
4831 }

4849 template<typename BasicJsonType> struct internal_iterator
4850 {
4852  typename BasicJsonType::object_t::iterator object_iterator {};
4854  typename BasicJsonType::array_t::iterator array_iterator {};
4856  primitive_iterator_t primitive_iterator {};

4908 template<typename BasicJsonType>
4909 class iter_impl
4910 {
4912  friend iter_impl<typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value, typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type, const BasicJsonType>::type>;
4913  friend BasicJsonType;
4914  friend iteration_proxy<iter_impl>;
4915 
4916  using object_t = typename BasicJsonType::object_t;
4917  using array_t = typename BasicJsonType::array_t;
4918  // make sure BasicJsonType is basic_json or const basic_json
4919  static_assert(is_basic_json<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>::value,
4920  "iter_impl only accepts (const) basic_json");
4921 
4922  public:
4923 
4929  using iterator_category = std::bidirectional_iterator_tag;
4930 
4932  using value_type = typename BasicJsonType::value_type;
4934  using difference_type = typename BasicJsonType::difference_type;
4936  using pointer = typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value,
4937  typename BasicJsonType::const_pointer,
4938  typename BasicJsonType::pointer>::type;
4940  using reference =
4941  typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value,
4942  typename BasicJsonType::const_reference,
4943  typename BasicJsonType::reference>::type;

4946  iter_impl() = default;
4947 
4954  explicit iter_impl(pointer object) noexcept : m_object(object)
4955  {
4956  assert(m_object != nullptr);
4957 
4958  switch (m_object->m_type)
4959  {
4960  case value_t::object:
4961  {
4962  m_it.object_iterator = typename object_t::iterator();
4963  break;
4964  }
4965 
4966  case value_t::array:
4967  {
4968  m_it.array_iterator = typename array_t::iterator();
4969  break;
4970  }
4971 
4972  default:
4973  {
4974  m_it.primitive_iterator = primitive_iterator_t();
4975  break;
4976  }
4977  }
4978  }

4994  iter_impl(const iter_impl<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>& other) noexcept
4995  : m_object(other.m_object), m_it(other.m_it) {}

5003  iter_impl& operator=(const iter_impl<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>& other) noexcept
5004  {
5005  m_object = other.m_object;
5006  m_it = other.m_it;
5007  return *this;
5008  }
5009 
5010  private:
5015  void set_begin() noexcept
5016  {
5017  assert(m_object != nullptr);
5018 
5019  switch (m_object->m_type)
5020  {
5021  case value_t::object:
5022  {
5023  m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->begin();
5024  break;
5025  }
5026 
5027  case value_t::array:
5028  {
5029  m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->begin();
5030  break;
5031  }
5032 
5033  case value_t::null:
5034  {
5035  // set to end so begin()==end() is true: null is empty
5036  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
5037  break;
5038  }
5039 
5040  default:
5041  {
5042  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_begin();
5043  break;
5044  }
5045  }
5046  }
5047 
5052  void set_end() noexcept
5053  {
5054  assert(m_object != nullptr);
5055 
5056  switch (m_object->m_type)
5057  {
5058  case value_t::object:
5059  {
5060  m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->end();
5061  break;
5062  }
5063 
5064  case value_t::array:
5065  {
5066  m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->end();
5067  break;
5068  }
5069 
5070  default:
5071  {
5072  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
5073  break;
5074  }
5075  }

5078  public:
5083  reference operator*() const
5084  {
5085  assert(m_object != nullptr);
5086 
5087  switch (m_object->m_type)
5088  {
5089  case value_t::object:
5090  {
5091  assert(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
5092  return m_it.object_iterator->second;
5093  }
5094 
5095  case value_t::array:
5096  {
5097  assert(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
5098  return *m_it.array_iterator;
5099  }
5100 
5101  case value_t::null:
5102  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
5103 
5104  default:
5105  {
5106  if (JSON_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin()))
5107  {
5108  return *m_object;
5109  }
5110 
5111  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
5112  }
5113  }
5114  }
5115 
5120  pointer operator->() const
5121  {
5122  assert(m_object != nullptr);
5123 
5124  switch (m_object->m_type)
5125  {
5126  case value_t::object:
5127  {
5128  assert(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
5129  return &(m_it.object_iterator->second);
5130  }
5131 
5132  case value_t::array:
5133  {
5134  assert(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
5135  return &*m_it.array_iterator;
5136  }
5137 
5138  default:
5139  {
5140  if (JSON_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin()))
5141  {
5142  return m_object;
5143  }
5144 
5145  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
5146  }
5147  }
5148  }

5174  break;

5178  {
5179  std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, 1);
5180  break;
5181  }
5182 
5183  default:
5184  {

5186  break;
5187  }
5188  }
5189

5209  {

5213  {
5214  case value_t::object:
5215  {
5216  std::advance(m_it.object_iterator, -1);
5217  break;
5218  }
5219 
5220  case value_t::array:
5221  {
5222  std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, -1);
5223  break;
5224  }
5225 
5226  default:

5229  break;
5230  }
5231  }
5232

5240  bool operator==(const iter_impl& other) const
5241  {
5242  // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
5243  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(m_object != other.m_object))
5244  {
5245  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers"));
5246  }
5247 
5248  assert(m_object != nullptr);
5249 
5250  switch (m_object->m_type)
5251  {
5252  case value_t::object:
5253  return (m_it.object_iterator == other.m_it.object_iterator);
5254 
5255  case value_t::array:
5256  return (m_it.array_iterator == other.m_it.array_iterator);
5257 
5258  default:
5259  return (m_it.primitive_iterator == other.m_it.primitive_iterator);
5260  }
5261  }
5262 
5267  bool operator!=(const iter_impl& other) const
5268  {
5269  return not operator==(other);
5270  }
5271 
5276  bool operator<(const iter_impl& other) const
5277  {
5278  // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
5279  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(m_object != other.m_object))
5280  {
5281  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers"));
5282  }
5283 
5284  assert(m_object != nullptr);
5285 
5286  switch (m_object->m_type)
5287  {
5288  case value_t::object:
5289  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(213, "cannot compare order of object iterators"));
5290 
5291  case value_t::array:
5292  return (m_it.array_iterator < other.m_it.array_iterator);
5293 
5294  default:
5295  return (m_it.primitive_iterator < other.m_it.primitive_iterator);
5296  }
5297  }

5427  {
5428  case value_t::object:
5429  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(208, "cannot use operator[] for object iterators"));
5430 
5431  case value_t::array:
5432  return *std::next(m_it.array_iterator, n);
5433 
5434  case value_t::null:

5472  }

5518 template<typename Base>
5519 class json_reverse_iterator : public std::reverse_iterator<Base>
5520 {
5521  public:
5522  using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
5524  using base_iterator = std::reverse_iterator<Base>;
5526  using reference = typename Base::reference;
5527 
5529  explicit json_reverse_iterator(const typename base_iterator::iterator_type& it) noexcept
5530  : base_iterator(it) {}
5531 
5533  explicit json_reverse_iterator(const base_iterator& it) noexcept : base_iterator(it) {}
5534 
5536  json_reverse_iterator const operator++(int)
5537  {
5538  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator++(1));
5539  }
5540 
5542  json_reverse_iterator& operator++()
5543  {
5544  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator++());
5545  }
5546 
5548  json_reverse_iterator const operator--(int)
5549  {
5550  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator--(1));
5551  }
5552 
5554  json_reverse_iterator& operator--()
5555  {
5556  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator--());
5557  }
5558 
5560  json_reverse_iterator& operator+=(difference_type i)
5561  {
5562  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator+=(i));
5563  }
5564 
5566  json_reverse_iterator operator+(difference_type i) const
5567  {
5568  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator+(i));
5569  }
5570 
5572  json_reverse_iterator operator-(difference_type i) const
5573  {
5574  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator-(i));
5575  }
5576 
5578  difference_type operator-(const json_reverse_iterator& other) const
5579  {
5580  return base_iterator(*this) - base_iterator(other);
5581  }
5582 
5584  reference operator[](difference_type n) const
5585  {
5586  return *(this->operator+(n));
5587  }
5588 
5590  auto key() const -> decltype(std::declval<Base>().key())
5591  {
5592  auto it = --this->base();
5593  return it.key();
5594  }
5595 
5597  reference value() const
5598  {
5599  auto it = --this->base();
5600  return it.operator * ();
5601  }
5602 };

5623 template<typename CharType> struct output_adapter_protocol
5624 {
5625  virtual void write_character(CharType c) = 0;
5626  virtual void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) = 0;
5627  virtual ~output_adapter_protocol() = default;
5628 };
5629 
5631 template<typename CharType>
5632 using output_adapter_t = std::shared_ptr<output_adapter_protocol<CharType>>;
5633 
5635 template<typename CharType>
5636 class output_vector_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
5637 {
5638  public:
5639  explicit output_vector_adapter(std::vector<CharType>& vec) : v(vec) {}
5640 
5641  void write_character(CharType c) override
5642  {
5643  v.push_back(c);
5644  }
5645 
5646  void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
5647  {
5648  std::copy(s, s + length, std::back_inserter(v));
5649  }
5650 
5651  private:
5652  std::vector<CharType>& v;
5653 };
5654 
5656 template<typename CharType>
5657 class output_stream_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
5658 {
5659  public:
5660  explicit output_stream_adapter(std::basic_ostream<CharType>& s) : stream(s) {}
5661 
5662  void write_character(CharType c) override
5663  {
5664  stream.put(c);
5665  }
5666 
5667  void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
5668  {
5669  stream.write(s, static_cast<std::streamsize>(length));
5670  }
5671 
5672  private:
5673  std::basic_ostream<CharType>& stream;
5674 };
5675 
5677 template<typename CharType, typename StringType = std::basic_string<CharType>>
5678 class output_string_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
5679 {
5680  public:
5681  explicit output_string_adapter(StringType& s) : str(s) {}
5682 
5683  void write_character(CharType c) override
5684  {
5685  str.push_back(c);
5686  }
5687 
5688  void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
5689  {
5690  str.append(s, length);
5691  }
5692 
5693  private:
5694  StringType& str;
5695 };

5708  : oa(std::make_shared<output_string_adapter<CharType, StringType>>(s)) {}

5753 // binary reader //
5755 
5759 template<typename BasicJsonType>
5760 class binary_reader
5761 {
5762  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
5763  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
5764  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
5765  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
5766  using json_sax_t = json_sax<BasicJsonType>;
5767 
5768  public:
5774  explicit binary_reader(input_adapter_t adapter) : ia(std::move(adapter))
5775  {
5776  assert(ia);
5777  }
5778 
5786  bool sax_parse(const input_format_t format,
5787  json_sax_t* sax_,
5788  const bool strict = true)
5789  {
5790  sax = sax_;
5791  bool result;
5792 
5793  switch (format)
5794  {
5795  case input_format_t::cbor:
5796  result = parse_cbor_internal();
5797  break;
5798 
5799  case input_format_t::msgpack:
5800  result = parse_msgpack_internal();
5801  break;
5802 
5803  case input_format_t::ubjson:
5804  result = parse_ubjson_internal();
5805  break;
5806 
5807  default:
5808  assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
5809  }
5810 
5811  // strict mode: next byte must be EOF
5812  if (result and strict)
5813  {
5814  if (format == input_format_t::ubjson)
5815  {
5816  get_ignore_noop();
5817  }
5818  else
5819  {
5820  get();
5821  }
5822 
5823  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof()))
5824  {
5825  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, get_token_string(), parse_error::create(110, chars_read, "expected end of input"));
5826  }
5827  }
5828 
5829  return result;
5830  }
5831 
5839  static constexpr bool little_endianess(int num = 1) noexcept
5840  {
5841  return (*reinterpret_cast<char*>(&num) == 1);
5842  }
5843 
5844  private:
5852  bool parse_cbor_internal(const bool get_char = true)
5853  {
5854  switch (get_char ? get() : current)
5855  {
5856  // EOF
5857  case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
5858  return unexpect_eof();
5859 
5860  // Integer 0x00..0x17 (0..23)
5861  case 0x00:
5862  case 0x01:
5863  case 0x02:
5864  case 0x03:
5865  case 0x04:
5866  case 0x05:
5867  case 0x06:
5868  case 0x07:
5869  case 0x08:
5870  case 0x09:
5871  case 0x0A:
5872  case 0x0B:
5873  case 0x0C:
5874  case 0x0D:
5875  case 0x0E:
5876  case 0x0F:
5877  case 0x10:
5878  case 0x11:
5879  case 0x12:
5880  case 0x13:
5881  case 0x14:
5882  case 0x15:
5883  case 0x16:
5884  case 0x17:
5885  return sax->number_unsigned(static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(current));
5886 
5887  case 0x18: // Unsigned integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
5888  {
5889  uint8_t number;
5890  return get_number(number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
5891  }
5892 
5893  case 0x19: // Unsigned integer (two-byte uint16_t follows)
5894  {
5895  uint16_t number;
5896  return get_number(number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
5897  }
5898 
5899  case 0x1A: // Unsigned integer (four-byte uint32_t follows)
5900  {
5901  uint32_t number;
5902  return get_number(number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
5903  }
5904 
5905  case 0x1B: // Unsigned integer (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
5906  {
5907  uint64_t number;
5908  return get_number(number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
5909  }
5910 
5911  // Negative integer -1-0x00..-1-0x17 (-1..-24)
5912  case 0x20:
5913  case 0x21:
5914  case 0x22:
5915  case 0x23:
5916  case 0x24:
5917  case 0x25:
5918  case 0x26:
5919  case 0x27:
5920  case 0x28:
5921  case 0x29:
5922  case 0x2A:
5923  case 0x2B:
5924  case 0x2C:
5925  case 0x2D:
5926  case 0x2E:
5927  case 0x2F:
5928  case 0x30:
5929  case 0x31:
5930  case 0x32:
5931  case 0x33:
5932  case 0x34:
5933  case 0x35:
5934  case 0x36:
5935  case 0x37:
5936  return sax->number_integer(static_cast<int8_t>(0x20 - 1 - current));
5937 
5938  case 0x38: // Negative integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
5939  {
5940  uint8_t number;
5941  return get_number(number) and sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
5942  }
5943 
5944  case 0x39: // Negative integer -1-n (two-byte uint16_t follows)
5945  {
5946  uint16_t number;
5947  return get_number(number) and sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
5948  }
5949 
5950  case 0x3A: // Negative integer -1-n (four-byte uint32_t follows)
5951  {
5952  uint32_t number;
5953  return get_number(number) and sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
5954  }
5955 
5956  case 0x3B: // Negative integer -1-n (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
5957  {
5958  uint64_t number;
5959  return get_number(number) and sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1)
5960  - static_cast<number_integer_t>(number));
5961  }
5962 
5963  // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
5964  case 0x60:
5965  case 0x61:
5966  case 0x62:
5967  case 0x63:
5968  case 0x64:
5969  case 0x65:
5970  case 0x66:
5971  case 0x67:
5972  case 0x68:
5973  case 0x69:
5974  case 0x6A:
5975  case 0x6B:
5976  case 0x6C:
5977  case 0x6D:
5978  case 0x6E:
5979  case 0x6F:
5980  case 0x70:
5981  case 0x71:
5982  case 0x72:
5983  case 0x73:
5984  case 0x74:
5985  case 0x75:
5986  case 0x76:
5987  case 0x77:
5988  case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
5989  case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
5990  case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
5991  case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
5992  case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
5993  {
5994  string_t s;
5995  return get_cbor_string(s) and sax->string(s);
5996  }
5997 
5998  // array (0x00..0x17 data items follow)
5999  case 0x80:
6000  case 0x81:
6001  case 0x82:
6002  case 0x83:
6003  case 0x84:
6004  case 0x85:
6005  case 0x86:
6006  case 0x87:
6007  case 0x88:
6008  case 0x89:
6009  case 0x8A:
6010  case 0x8B:
6011  case 0x8C:
6012  case 0x8D:
6013  case 0x8E:
6014  case 0x8F:
6015  case 0x90:
6016  case 0x91:
6017  case 0x92:
6018  case 0x93:
6019  case 0x94:
6020  case 0x95:
6021  case 0x96:
6022  case 0x97:
6023  return get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(current & 0x1F));
6024 
6025  case 0x98: // array (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
6026  {
6027  uint8_t len;
6028  return get_number(len) and get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
6029  }
6030 
6031  case 0x99: // array (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
6032  {
6033  uint16_t len;
6034  return get_number(len) and get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
6035  }
6036 
6037  case 0x9A: // array (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
6038  {
6039  uint32_t len;
6040  return get_number(len) and get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
6041  }
6042 
6043  case 0x9B: // array (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
6044  {
6045  uint64_t len;
6046  return get_number(len) and get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
6047  }
6048 
6049  case 0x9F: // array (indefinite length)
6050  return get_cbor_array(json_sax_t::no_limit);
6051 
6052  // map (0x00..0x17 pairs of data items follow)
6053  case 0xA0:
6054  case 0xA1:
6055  case 0xA2:
6056  case 0xA3:
6057  case 0xA4:
6058  case 0xA5:
6059  case 0xA6:
6060  case 0xA7:
6061  case 0xA8:
6062  case 0xA9:
6063  case 0xAA:
6064  case 0xAB:
6065  case 0xAC:
6066  case 0xAD:
6067  case 0xAE:
6068  case 0xAF:
6069  case 0xB0:
6070  case 0xB1:
6071  case 0xB2:
6072  case 0xB3:
6073  case 0xB4:
6074  case 0xB5:
6075  case 0xB6:
6076  case 0xB7:
6077  return get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(current & 0x1F));
6078 
6079  case 0xB8: // map (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
6080  {
6081  uint8_t len;
6082  return get_number(len) and get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
6083  }
6084 
6085  case 0xB9: // map (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
6086  {
6087  uint16_t len;
6088  return get_number(len) and get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
6089  }
6090 
6091  case 0xBA: // map (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
6092  {
6093  uint32_t len;
6094  return get_number(len) and get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
6095  }
6096 
6097  case 0xBB: // map (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
6098  {
6099  uint64_t len;
6100  return get_number(len) and get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
6101  }
6102 
6103  case 0xBF: // map (indefinite length)
6104  return get_cbor_object(json_sax_t::no_limit);
6105 
6106  case 0xF4: // false
6107  return sax->boolean(false);
6108 
6109  case 0xF5: // true
6110  return sax->boolean(true);
6111 
6112  case 0xF6: // null
6113  return sax->null();
6114 
6115  case 0xF9: // Half-Precision Float (two-byte IEEE 754)
6116  {
6117  const int byte1 = get();
6118  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof()))
6119  {
6120  return false;
6121  }
6122  const int byte2 = get();
6123  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof()))
6124  {
6125  return false;
6126  }
6127 
6128  // code from RFC 7049, Appendix D, Figure 3:
6129  // As half-precision floating-point numbers were only added
6130  // to IEEE 754 in 2008, today's programming platforms often
6131  // still only have limited support for them. It is very
6132  // easy to include at least decoding support for them even
6133  // without such support. An example of a small decoder for
6134  // half-precision floating-point numbers in the C language
6135  // is shown in Fig. 3.
6136  const int half = (byte1 << 8) + byte2;
6137  const double val = [&half]
6138  {
6139  const int exp = (half >> 10) & 0x1F;
6140  const int mant = half & 0x3FF;
6141  assert(0 <= exp and exp <= 32);
6142  assert(0 <= mant and mant <= 1024);
6143  switch (exp)
6144  {
6145  case 0:
6146  return std::ldexp(mant, -24);
6147  case 31:
6148  return (mant == 0)
6149  ? std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity()
6150  : std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
6151  default:
6152  return std::ldexp(mant + 1024, exp - 25);
6153  }
6154  }();
6155  return sax->number_float((half & 0x8000) != 0
6156  ? static_cast<number_float_t>(-val)
6157  : static_cast<number_float_t>(val), "");
6158  }
6159 
6160  case 0xFA: // Single-Precision Float (four-byte IEEE 754)
6161  {
6162  float number;
6163  return get_number(number) and sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
6164  }
6165 
6166  case 0xFB: // Double-Precision Float (eight-byte IEEE 754)
6167  {
6168  double number;
6169  return get_number(number) and sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
6170  }
6171 
6172  default: // anything else (0xFF is handled inside the other types)
6173  {
6174  auto last_token = get_token_string();
6175  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, "error reading CBOR; last byte: 0x" + last_token));
6176  }
6177  }
6178  }

6563  int get()

6572  int get_ignore_noop()
6573  {
6574  do
6575  {
6576  get();
6577  }
6578  while (current == 'N');
6579 
6580  return current;
6581  }
6582 
6583  /*
6584  @brief read a number from the input
6585 
6586  @tparam NumberType the type of the number
6587  @param[out] result number of type @a NumberType
6588 
6589  @return whether conversion completed
6590 
6591  @note This function needs to respect the system's endianess, because
6592  bytes in CBOR, MessagePack, and UBJSON are stored in network order
6593  (big endian) and therefore need reordering on little endian systems.
6594  */
6595  template<typename NumberType>
6596  bool get_number(NumberType& result)
6597  {
6598  // step 1: read input into array with system's byte order
6599  std::array<uint8_t, sizeof(NumberType)> vec;
6600  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(NumberType); ++i)
6601  {
6602  get();
6603  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof()))
6604  {
6605  return false;
6606  }
6607 
6608  // reverse byte order prior to conversion if necessary
6609  if (is_little_endian)
6610  {
6611  vec[sizeof(NumberType) - i - 1] = static_cast<uint8_t>(current);
6612  }
6613  else
6614  {
6615  vec[i] = static_cast<uint8_t>(current); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
6616  }
6617  }
6618 
6619  // step 2: convert array into number of type T and return
6620  std::memcpy(&result, vec.data(), sizeof(NumberType));
6621  return true;
6622  }
6623 
6637  template<typename NumberType>
6638  bool get_string(const NumberType len, string_t& result)
6639  {
6640  bool success = true;
6641  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(result), len, [this, &success]()
6642  {
6643  get();
6644  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof()))
6645  {
6646  success = false;
6647  }
6648  return static_cast<char>(current);
6649  });
6650  return success;
6651  }
6652 
6664  bool get_cbor_string(string_t& result)
6665  {
6666  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof()))
6667  {
6668  return false;
6669  }
6670 
6671  switch (current)
6672  {
6673  // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
6674  case 0x60:
6675  case 0x61:
6676  case 0x62:
6677  case 0x63:
6678  case 0x64:
6679  case 0x65:
6680  case 0x66:
6681  case 0x67:
6682  case 0x68:
6683  case 0x69:
6684  case 0x6A:
6685  case 0x6B:
6686  case 0x6C:
6687  case 0x6D:
6688  case 0x6E:
6689  case 0x6F:
6690  case 0x70:
6691  case 0x71:
6692  case 0x72:
6693  case 0x73:
6694  case 0x74:
6695  case 0x75:
6696  case 0x76:
6697  case 0x77:
6698  {
6699  return get_string(current & 0x1F, result);
6700  }
6701 
6702  case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
6703  {
6704  uint8_t len;
6705  return get_number(len) and get_string(len, result);
6706  }
6707 
6708  case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
6709  {
6710  uint16_t len;
6711  return get_number(len) and get_string(len, result);
6712  }
6713 
6714  case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
6715  {
6716  uint32_t len;
6717  return get_number(len) and get_string(len, result);
6718  }
6719 
6720  case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
6721  {
6722  uint64_t len;
6723  return get_number(len) and get_string(len, result);
6724  }
6725 
6726  case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
6727  {
6728  while (get() != 0xFF)
6729  {
6730  string_t chunk;
6731  if (not get_cbor_string(chunk))
6732  {
6733  return false;
6734  }
6735  result.append(chunk);
6736  }
6737  return true;
6738  }
6739 
6740  default:
6741  {
6742  auto last_token = get_token_string();
6743  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, "expected a CBOR string; last byte: 0x" + last_token));
6744  }
6745  }
6746  }
6747 
6753  bool get_cbor_array(const std::size_t len)
6754  {
6755  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(len)))
6756  {
6757  return false;
6758  }
6759 
6760  if (len != json_sax_t::no_limit)
6761  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
6762  {
6763  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_cbor_internal()))
6764  {
6765  return false;
6766  }
6767  }
6768  else
6769  {
6770  while (get() != 0xFF)
6771  {
6772  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_cbor_internal(false)))
6773  {
6774  return false;
6775  }
6776  }
6777  }
6778 
6779  return sax->end_array();
6780  }
6781 
6787  bool get_cbor_object(const std::size_t len)
6788  {
6789  if (not JSON_UNLIKELY(sax->start_object(len)))
6790  {
6791  return false;
6792  }
6793 
6794  string_t key;
6795  if (len != json_sax_t::no_limit)
6796  {
6797  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
6798  {
6799  get();
6800  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_cbor_string(key) or not sax->key(key)))
6801  {
6802  return false;
6803  }
6804 
6805  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_cbor_internal()))
6806  {
6807  return false;
6808  }
6809  key.clear();
6810  }
6811  }
6812  else
6813  {
6814  while (get() != 0xFF)
6815  {
6816  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_cbor_string(key) or not sax->key(key)))
6817  {
6818  return false;
6819  }
6820 
6821  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_cbor_internal()))
6822  {
6823  return false;
6824  }
6825  key.clear();
6826  }
6827  }
6828 
6829  return sax->end_object();
6830  }
6831 
6842  bool get_msgpack_string(string_t& result)
6843  {
6844  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof()))
6845  {
6846  return false;
6847  }
6848 
6849  switch (current)
6850  {
6851  // fixstr
6852  case 0xA0:
6853  case 0xA1:
6854  case 0xA2:
6855  case 0xA3:
6856  case 0xA4:
6857  case 0xA5:
6858  case 0xA6:
6859  case 0xA7:
6860  case 0xA8:
6861  case 0xA9:
6862  case 0xAA:
6863  case 0xAB:
6864  case 0xAC:
6865  case 0xAD:
6866  case 0xAE:
6867  case 0xAF:
6868  case 0xB0:
6869  case 0xB1:
6870  case 0xB2:
6871  case 0xB3:
6872  case 0xB4:
6873  case 0xB5:
6874  case 0xB6:
6875  case 0xB7:
6876  case 0xB8:
6877  case 0xB9:
6878  case 0xBA:
6879  case 0xBB:
6880  case 0xBC:
6881  case 0xBD:
6882  case 0xBE:
6883  case 0xBF:
6884  {
6885  return get_string(current & 0x1F, result);
6886  }
6887 
6888  case 0xD9: // str 8
6889  {
6890  uint8_t len;
6891  return get_number(len) and get_string(len, result);
6892  }
6893 
6894  case 0xDA: // str 16
6895  {
6896  uint16_t len;
6897  return get_number(len) and get_string(len, result);
6898  }
6899 
6900  case 0xDB: // str 32
6901  {
6902  uint32_t len;
6903  return get_number(len) and get_string(len, result);
6904  }
6905 
6906  default:
6907  {
6908  auto last_token = get_token_string();
6909  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, "expected a MessagePack string; last byte: 0x" + last_token));
6910  }
6911  }
6912  }
6913 
6918  bool get_msgpack_array(const std::size_t len)
6919  {
6920  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(len)))
6921  {
6922  return false;
6923  }
6924 
6925  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
6926  {
6927  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_msgpack_internal()))
6928  {
6929  return false;
6930  }
6931  }
6932 
6933  return sax->end_array();
6934  }
6935 
6940  bool get_msgpack_object(const std::size_t len)
6941  {
6942  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(len)))
6943  {
6944  return false;
6945  }
6946 
6947  string_t key;
6948  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
6949  {
6950  get();
6951  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_msgpack_string(key) or not sax->key(key)))
6952  {
6953  return false;
6954  }
6955 
6956  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_msgpack_internal()))
6957  {
6958  return false;
6959  }
6960  key.clear();
6961  }
6962 
6963  return sax->end_object();

6965 
6980  bool get_ubjson_string(string_t& result, const bool get_char = true)
6981  {
6982  if (get_char)
6983  {
6984  get(); // TODO: may we ignore N here?
6985  }
6986 
6987  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof()))
6988  {
6989  return false;
6990  }
6991 
6992  switch (current)
6993  {
6994  case 'U':
6995  {
6996  uint8_t len;
6997  return get_number(len) and get_string(len, result);
6998  }
6999 
7000  case 'i':
7001  {
7002  int8_t len;
7003  return get_number(len) and get_string(len, result);
7004  }
7005 
7006  case 'I':
7007  {
7008  int16_t len;
7009  return get_number(len) and get_string(len, result);
7010  }
7011 
7012  case 'l':
7013  {
7014  int32_t len;
7015  return get_number(len) and get_string(len, result);
7016  }
7017 
7018  case 'L':
7019  {
7020  int64_t len;
7021  return get_number(len) and get_string(len, result);
7022  }
7023 
7024  default:
7025  auto last_token = get_token_string();
7026  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, "expected a UBJSON string; last byte: 0x" + last_token));
7027  }
7028  }
7029 
7034  bool get_ubjson_size_value(std::size_t& result)
7035  {
7036  switch (get_ignore_noop())
7037  {
7038  case 'U':
7039  {
7040  uint8_t number;
7041  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_number(number)))
7042  {
7043  return false;
7044  }
7045  result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
7046  return true;
7047  }
7048 
7049  case 'i':
7050  {
7051  int8_t number;
7052  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_number(number)))
7053  {
7054  return false;
7055  }
7056  result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
7057  return true;
7058  }
7059 
7060  case 'I':
7061  {
7062  int16_t number;
7063  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_number(number)))
7064  {
7065  return false;
7066  }
7067  result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
7068  return true;
7069  }
7070 
7071  case 'l':
7072  {
7073  int32_t number;
7074  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_number(number)))
7075  {
7076  return false;
7077  }
7078  result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
7079  return true;
7080  }
7081 
7082  case 'L':
7083  {
7084  int64_t number;
7085  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_number(number)))
7086  {
7087  return false;
7088  }
7089  result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
7090  return true;
7091  }
7092 
7093  default:
7094  {
7095  auto last_token = get_token_string();
7096  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, "byte after '#' must denote a number type; last byte: 0x" + last_token));
7097  }
7098  }
7099  }
7100 
7111  bool get_ubjson_size_type(std::pair<std::size_t, int>& result)
7112  {
7113  result.first = string_t::npos; // size
7114  result.second = 0; // type
7115 
7116  get_ignore_noop();
7117 
7118  if (current == '$')
7119  {
7120  result.second = get(); // must not ignore 'N', because 'N' maybe the type
7121  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof()))
7122  {
7123  return false;
7124  }
7125 
7126  get_ignore_noop();
7127  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current != '#'))
7128  {
7129  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof()))
7130  {
7131  return false;
7132  }
7133  auto last_token = get_token_string();
7134  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, "expected '#' after UBJSON type information; last byte: 0x" + last_token));
7135  }
7136 
7137  return get_ubjson_size_value(result.first);
7138  }
7139  else if (current == '#')
7140  {
7141  return get_ubjson_size_value(result.first);
7142  }
7143  return true;
7144  }
7145 
7150  bool get_ubjson_value(const int prefix)
7151  {
7152  switch (prefix)
7153  {
7154  case std::char_traits<char>::eof(): // EOF
7155  return unexpect_eof();
7156 
7157  case 'T': // true
7158  return sax->boolean(true);
7159  case 'F': // false
7160  return sax->boolean(false);
7161 
7162  case 'Z': // null
7163  return sax->null();
7164 
7165  case 'U':
7166  {
7167  uint8_t number;
7168  return get_number(number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
7169  }
7170 
7171  case 'i':
7172  {
7173  int8_t number;
7174  return get_number(number) and sax->number_integer(number);
7175  }
7176 
7177  case 'I':
7178  {
7179  int16_t number;
7180  return get_number(number) and sax->number_integer(number);
7181  }
7182 
7183  case 'l':
7184  {
7185  int32_t number;
7186  return get_number(number) and sax->number_integer(number);
7187  }
7188 
7189  case 'L':
7190  {
7191  int64_t number;
7192  return get_number(number) and sax->number_integer(number);
7193  }
7194 
7195  case 'd':
7196  {
7197  float number;
7198  return get_number(number) and sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
7199  }
7200 
7201  case 'D':
7202  {
7203  double number;
7204  return get_number(number) and sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
7205  }
7206 
7207  case 'C': // char
7208  {
7209  get();
7210  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof()))
7211  {
7212  return false;
7213  }
7214  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current > 127))
7215  {
7216  auto last_token = get_token_string();
7217  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, "byte after 'C' must be in range 0x00..0x7F; last byte: 0x" + last_token));
7218  }
7219  string_t s(1, static_cast<char>(current));
7220  return sax->string(s);
7221  }
7222 
7223  case 'S': // string
7224  {
7225  string_t s;
7226  return get_ubjson_string(s) and sax->string(s);
7227  }
7228 
7229  case '[': // array
7230  return get_ubjson_array();
7231 
7232  case '{': // object
7233  return get_ubjson_object();
7234 
7235  default: // anything else
7236  {
7237  auto last_token = get_token_string();
7238  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, "error reading UBJSON; last byte: 0x" + last_token));
7239  }
7240  }
7241  }
7242 
7246  bool get_ubjson_array()
7247  {
7248  std::pair<std::size_t, int> size_and_type;
7249  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_size_type(size_and_type)))
7250  {
7251  return false;
7252  }
7253 
7254  if (size_and_type.first != string_t::npos)
7255  {
7256  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(size_and_type.first)))
7257  {
7258  return false;
7259  }
7260 
7261  if (size_and_type.second != 0)
7262  {
7263  if (size_and_type.second != 'N')
7264  {
7265  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
7266  {
7267  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_value(size_and_type.second)))
7268  {
7269  return false;
7270  }
7271  }
7272  }
7273  }
7274  else
7275  {
7276  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
7277  {
7278  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_ubjson_internal()))
7279  {
7280  return false;
7281  }
7282  }
7283  }
7284  }
7285  else
7286  {
7287  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array()))
7288  {
7289  return false;
7290  }
7291 
7292  while (current != ']')
7293  {
7294  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_ubjson_internal(false)))
7295  {
7296  return false;
7297  }
7298  get_ignore_noop();
7299  }
7300  }
7301 
7302  return sax->end_array();
7303  }
7304 
7308  bool get_ubjson_object()
7309  {
7310  std::pair<std::size_t, int> size_and_type;
7311  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_size_type(size_and_type)))
7312  {
7313  return false;
7314  }
7315 
7316  string_t key;
7317  if (size_and_type.first != string_t::npos)
7318  {
7319  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(size_and_type.first)))
7320  {
7321  return false;
7322  }
7323 
7324  if (size_and_type.second != 0)
7325  {
7326  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
7327  {
7328  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_string(key) or not sax->key(key)))
7329  {
7330  return false;
7331  }
7332  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_value(size_and_type.second)))
7333  {
7334  return false;
7335  }
7336  key.clear();
7337  }
7338  }
7339  else
7340  {
7341  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
7342  {
7343  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_string(key) or not sax->key(key)))
7344  {
7345  return false;
7346  }
7347  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_ubjson_internal()))
7348  {
7349  return false;
7350  }
7351  key.clear();
7352  }
7353  }
7354  }
7355  else
7356  {
7357  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object()))
7358  {
7359  return false;
7360  }
7361 
7362  while (current != '}')
7363  {
7364  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_string(key, false) or not sax->key(key)))
7365  {
7366  return false;
7367  }
7368  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_ubjson_internal()))
7369  {
7370  return false;
7371  }
7372  get_ignore_noop();
7373  key.clear();
7374  }
7375  }
7376 
7377  return sax->end_object();
7378  }
7379 
7383  bool unexpect_eof() const
7384  {
7385  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current == std::char_traits<char>::eof()))
7386  {
7387  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, "<end of file>", parse_error::create(110, chars_read, "unexpected end of input"));
7388  }
7389  return true;
7390  }
7391 
7395  std::string get_token_string() const
7396  {
7397  char cr[3];
7398  snprintf(cr, 3, "%.2hhX", static_cast<unsigned char>(current));
7399  return std::string{cr};
7400  }
7401 
7402  private:
7404  input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
7405 
7407  int current = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
7408 
7410  std::size_t chars_read = 0;
7411 
7413  const bool is_little_endian = little_endianess();
7414 
7416  json_sax_t* sax = nullptr;
7417 };
7418 }
7419 }

7424 #include <algorithm> // reverse
7425 #include <array> // array
7426 #include <cstdint> // uint8_t, uint16_t, uint32_t, uint64_t
7427 #include <cstring> // memcpy
7428 #include <limits> // numeric_limits
7429

7432 // #include <nlohmann/detail/output/output_adapters.hpp>
