10176 #include <cassert> // assert
10177 #include <numeric> // accumulate
10178 #include <string> // string
10179 #include <vector> // vector
10180 
10181 // #include <nlohmann/detail/macro_scope.hpp>
10182 
10183 // #include <nlohmann/detail/exceptions.hpp>
10184 
10185 // #include <nlohmann/detail/value_t.hpp>
10186 
10187 
10188 namespace nlohmann
10189 {
10190 template<typename BasicJsonType>
10191 class json_pointer
10192 {
10193  // allow basic_json to access private members
10194  NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL_DECLARATION
10195  friend class basic_json;
10196 
10197  public:
10219  explicit json_pointer(const std::string& s = "")
10220  : reference_tokens(split(s))
10221  {}
10222 
10238  std::string to_string() const noexcept
10239  {
10240  return std::accumulate(reference_tokens.begin(), reference_tokens.end(),
10241  std::string{},
10242  [](const std::string & a, const std::string & b)
10243  {
10244  return a + "/" + escape(b);
10245  });
10246  }
10247 
10249  operator std::string() const
10250  {
10251  return to_string();
10252  }
10253 
10261  static int array_index(const std::string& s)
10262  {
10263  std::size_t processed_chars = 0;
10264  const int res = std::stoi(s, &processed_chars);
10265 
10266  // check if the string was completely read
10267  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(processed_chars != s.size()))
10268  {
10269  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + s + "'"));
10270  }
10271 
10272  return res;
10273  }
10274 
10275  private:
10280  std::string pop_back()
10281  {
10282  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(is_root()))
10283  {
10284  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(405, "JSON pointer has no parent"));
10285  }
10286 
10287  auto last = reference_tokens.back();
10288  reference_tokens.pop_back();
10289  return last;
10290  }
10291 
10293  bool is_root() const
10294  {
10295  return reference_tokens.empty();
10296  }
10297 
10298  json_pointer top() const
10299  {
10300  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(is_root()))
10301  {
10302  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(405, "JSON pointer has no parent"));
10303  }
10304 
10305  json_pointer result = *this;
10306  result.reference_tokens = {reference_tokens[0]};
10307  return result;
10308  }
10309 
10318  BasicJsonType& get_and_create(BasicJsonType& j) const
10319  {
10320  using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
10321  auto result = &j;
10322 
10323  // in case no reference tokens exist, return a reference to the JSON value
10324  // j which will be overwritten by a primitive value
10325  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
10326  {
10327  switch (result->m_type)
10328  {
10329  case detail::value_t::null:
10330  {
10331  if (reference_token == "0")
10332  {
10333  // start a new array if reference token is 0
10334  result = &result->operator[](0);
10335  }
10336  else
10337  {
10338  // start a new object otherwise
10339  result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
10340  }
10341  break;
10342  }
10343 
10344  case detail::value_t::object:
10345  {
10346  // create an entry in the object
10347  result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
10348  break;
10349  }
10350 
10351  case detail::value_t::array:
10352  {
10353  // create an entry in the array
10354  JSON_TRY
10355  {
10356  result = &result->operator[](static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token)));
10357  }
10358  JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&)
10359  {
10360  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
10361  }
10362  break;
10363  }
10364 
10365  /*
10366  The following code is only reached if there exists a reference
10367  token _and_ the current value is primitive. In this case, we have
10368  an error situation, because primitive values may only occur as
10369  single value; that is, with an empty list of reference tokens.
10370  */
10371  default:
10372  JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(313, "invalid value to unflatten"));
10373  }
10374  }
10375 
10376  return *result;
10377  }
10378 
10398  BasicJsonType& get_unchecked(BasicJsonType* ptr) const
10399  {
10400  using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
10401  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
10402  {
10403  // convert null values to arrays or objects before continuing
10404  if (ptr->m_type == detail::value_t::null)
10405  {
10406  // check if reference token is a number
10407  const bool nums =
10408  std::all_of(reference_token.begin(), reference_token.end(),
10409  [](const char x)
10410  {
10411  return (x >= '0' and x <= '9');
10412  });
10413 
10414  // change value to array for numbers or "-" or to object otherwise
10415  *ptr = (nums or reference_token == "-")
10416  ? detail::value_t::array
10417  : detail::value_t::object;
10418  }
10419 
10420  switch (ptr->m_type)
10421  {
10422  case detail::value_t::object:
10423  {
10424  // use unchecked object access
10425  ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
10426  break;
10427  }
10428 
10429  case detail::value_t::array:
10430  {
10431  // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
10432  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0'))
10433  {
10434  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(106, 0,
10435  "array index '" + reference_token +
10436  "' must not begin with '0'"));
10437  }
10438 
10439  if (reference_token == "-")
10440  {
10441  // explicitly treat "-" as index beyond the end
10442  ptr = &ptr->operator[](ptr->m_value.array->size());
10443  }
10444  else
10445  {
10446  // convert array index to number; unchecked access
10447  JSON_TRY
10448  {
10449  ptr = &ptr->operator[](
10450  static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token)));
10451  }
10452  JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&)
10453  {
10454  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
10455  }
10456  }
10457  break;
10458  }
10459 
10460  default:
10461  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
10462  }
10463  }
10464 
10465  return *ptr;
10466  }
10467 
10474  BasicJsonType& get_checked(BasicJsonType* ptr) const
10475  {
10476  using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
10477  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
10478  {
10479  switch (ptr->m_type)
10480  {
10481  case detail::value_t::object:
10482  {
10483  // note: at performs range check
10484  ptr = &ptr->at(reference_token);
10485  break;
10486  }
10487 
10488  case detail::value_t::array:
10489  {
10490  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-"))
10491  {
10492  // "-" always fails the range check
10493  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(402,
10494  "array index '-' (" + std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) +
10495  ") is out of range"));
10496  }
10497 
10498  // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
10499  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0'))
10500  {
10501  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(106, 0,
10502  "array index '" + reference_token +
10503  "' must not begin with '0'"));
10504  }
10505 
10506  // note: at performs range check
10507  JSON_TRY
10508  {
10509  ptr = &ptr->at(static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token)));
10510  }
10511  JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&)
10512  {
10513  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
10514  }
10515  break;
10516  }
10517 
10518  default:
10519  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
10520  }
10521  }
10522 
10523  return *ptr;
10524  }
10525 
10539  const BasicJsonType& get_unchecked(const BasicJsonType* ptr) const
10540  {
10541  using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
10542  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
10543  {
10544  switch (ptr->m_type)
10545  {
10546  case detail::value_t::object:
10547  {
10548  // use unchecked object access
10549  ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
10550  break;
10551  }
10552 
10553  case detail::value_t::array:
10554  {
10555  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-"))
10556  {
10557  // "-" cannot be used for const access
10558  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(402,
10559  "array index '-' (" + std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) +
10560  ") is out of range"));
10561  }
10562

10575  static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token)));
10576  }

10580  }

10586  }
10587  }

10590  }
10591

10649 
10659  static std::vector<std::string> split(const std::string& reference_string)
10660  {
10661  std::vector<std::string> result;
10662 
10663  // special case: empty reference string -> no reference tokens
10664  if (reference_string.empty())
10665  {
10666  return result;
10667  }
10668 
10669  // check if nonempty reference string begins with slash
10670  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_string[0] != '/'))
10671  {
10672  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(107, 1,
10673  "JSON pointer must be empty or begin with '/' - was: '" +
10674  reference_string + "'"));
10675  }
10676 
10677  // extract the reference tokens:
10678  // - slash: position of the last read slash (or end of string)
10679  // - start: position after the previous slash
10680  for (
10681  // search for the first slash after the first character
10682  std::size_t slash = reference_string.find_first_of('/', 1),
10683  // set the beginning of the first reference token
10684  start = 1;
10685  // we can stop if start == string::npos+1 = 0
10686  start != 0;
10687  // set the beginning of the next reference token
10688  // (will eventually be 0 if slash == std::string::npos)
10689  start = slash + 1,
10690  // find next slash
10691  slash = reference_string.find_first_of('/', start))
10692  {
10693  // use the text between the beginning of the reference token
10694  // (start) and the last slash (slash).
10695  auto reference_token = reference_string.substr(start, slash - start);
10696 
10697  // check reference tokens are properly escaped
10698  for (std::size_t pos = reference_token.find_first_of('~');
10699  pos != std::string::npos;
10700  pos = reference_token.find_first_of('~', pos + 1))
10701  {
10702  assert(reference_token[pos] == '~');
10703 
10704  // ~ must be followed by 0 or 1
10705  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(pos == reference_token.size() - 1 or
10706  (reference_token[pos + 1] != '0' and
10707  reference_token[pos + 1] != '1')))
10708  {
10709  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(108, 0, "escape character '~' must be followed with '0' or '1'"));
10710  }
10711  }
10712 
10713  // finally, store the reference token
10714  unescape(reference_token);
10715  result.push_back(reference_token);
10716  }
10717 
10718  return result;
10719  }
10720 
10734  static void replace_substring(std::string& s, const std::string& f,
10735  const std::string& t)
10736  {
10737  assert(not f.empty());
10738  for (auto pos = s.find(f); // find first occurrence of f
10739  pos != std::string::npos; // make sure f was found
10740  s.replace(pos, f.size(), t), // replace with t, and
10741  pos = s.find(f, pos + t.size())) // find next occurrence of f
10742  {}
10743  }
10744 
10746  static std::string escape(std::string s)
10747  {
10748  replace_substring(s, "~", "~0");
10749  replace_substring(s, "/", "~1");
10750  return s;
10751  }
10752 
10754  static void unescape(std::string& s)
10755  {
10756  replace_substring(s, "~1", "/");
10757  replace_substring(s, "~0", "~");
10758  }
10759 
10767  static void flatten(const std::string& reference_string,
10768  const BasicJsonType& value,
10769  BasicJsonType& result)
10770  {
10771  switch (value.m_type)
10772  {
10773  case detail::value_t::array:
10774  {
10775  if (value.m_value.array->empty())
10776  {
10777  // flatten empty array as null
10778  result[reference_string] = nullptr;
10779  }
10780  else
10781  {
10782  // iterate array and use index as reference string
10783  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < value.m_value.array->size(); ++i)
10784  {
10785  flatten(reference_string + "/" + std::to_string(i),
10786  value.m_value.array->operator[](i), result);
10787  }
10788  }
10789  break;
10790  }
10791 
10792  case detail::value_t::object:
10793  {
10794  if (value.m_value.object->empty())
10795  {
10796  // flatten empty object as null
10797  result[reference_string] = nullptr;
10798  }
10799  else
10800  {
10801  // iterate object and use keys as reference string
10802  for (const auto& element : *value.m_value.object)
10803  {
10804  flatten(reference_string + "/" + escape(element.first), element.second, result);
10805  }
10806  }
10807  break;
10808  }
10809 
10810  default:
10811  {
10812  // add primitive value with its reference string
10813  result[reference_string] = value;
10814  break;
10815  }
10816  }
10817  }
10818 
10829  static BasicJsonType
10830  unflatten(const BasicJsonType& value)
10831  {
10832  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not value.is_object()))
10833  {
10834  JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(314, "only objects can be unflattened"));
10835  }
10836 
10837  BasicJsonType result;
10838 
10839  // iterate the JSON object values
10840  for (const auto& element : *value.m_value.object)
10841  {
10842  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not element.second.is_primitive()))
10843  {
10844  JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(315, "values in object must be primitive"));
10845  }
10846 
10847  // assign value to reference pointed to by JSON pointer; Note that if
10848  // the JSON pointer is "" (i.e., points to the whole value), function
10849  // get_and_create returns a reference to result itself. An assignment
10850  // will then create a primitive value.
10851  json_pointer(element.first).get_and_create(result) = element.second;
10852  }
10853 
10854  return result;
10855  }
10856 
10857  friend bool operator==(json_pointer const& lhs,
10858  json_pointer const& rhs) noexcept
10859  {
10860  return (lhs.reference_tokens == rhs.reference_tokens);
10861  }
10862 
10863  friend bool operator!=(json_pointer const& lhs,
10864  json_pointer const& rhs) noexcept
10865  {
10866  return not (lhs == rhs);
10867  }
10868 
10870  std::vector<std::string> reference_tokens;
10871 };
10872 }

11668 
11670  template<typename T, typename... Args>
11671  static T* create(Args&& ... args)
11672  {
11673  AllocatorType<T> alloc;
11674  using AllocatorTraits = std::allocator_traits<AllocatorType<T>>;
11675 
11676  auto deleter = [&](T * object)
11677  {
11678  AllocatorTraits::deallocate(alloc, object, 1);
11679  };
11680  std::unique_ptr<T, decltype(deleter)> object(AllocatorTraits::allocate(alloc, 1), deleter);
11681  AllocatorTraits::construct(alloc, object.get(), std::forward<Args>(args)...);
11682  assert(object != nullptr);
11683  return object.release();
11684  }

11714  union json_value
11715  {
11717  object_t* object;
11719  array_t* array;
11721  string_t* string;
11723  boolean_t boolean;
11725  number_integer_t number_integer;
11727  number_unsigned_t number_unsigned;
11729  number_float_t number_float;
11730 
11732  json_value() = default;
11734  json_value(boolean_t v) noexcept : boolean(v) {}
11736  json_value(number_integer_t v) noexcept : number_integer(v) {}
11738  json_value(number_unsigned_t v) noexcept : number_unsigned(v) {}
11740  json_value(number_float_t v) noexcept : number_float(v) {}
11742  json_value(value_t t)
11743  {
11744  switch (t)
11745  {
11746  case value_t::object:
11747  {
11748  object = create<object_t>();
11749  break;
11750  }
11751 
11752  case value_t::array:
11753  {
11754  array = create<array_t>();
11755  break;
11756  }
11757 
11758  case value_t::string:
11759  {
11760  string = create<string_t>("");
11761  break;
11762  }
11763 
11764  case value_t::boolean:
11765  {
11766  boolean = boolean_t(false);
11767  break;
11768  }
11769 
11770  case value_t::number_integer:
11771  {
11772  number_integer = number_integer_t(0);
11773  break;
11774  }
11775 
11776  case value_t::number_unsigned:
11777  {
11778  number_unsigned = number_unsigned_t(0);
11779  break;
11780  }
11781 
11782  case value_t::number_float:
11783  {
11784  number_float = number_float_t(0.0);
11785  break;
11786  }
11787 
11788  case value_t::null:
11789  {
11790  object = nullptr; // silence warning, see #821
11791  break;
11792  }
11793 
11794  default:
11795  {
11796  object = nullptr; // silence warning, see #821
11797  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(t == value_t::null))
11798  {
11799  JSON_THROW(other_error::create(500, "961c151d2e87f2686a955a9be24d316f1362bf21 3.1.2")); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
11800  }
11801  break;
11802  }
11803  }
11804  }
11805 
11807  json_value(const string_t& value)
11808  {
11809  string = create<string_t>(value);
11810  }
11811 
11813  json_value(string_t&& value)
11814  {
11815  string = create<string_t>(std::move(value));
11816  }

11834  }
11835

11838  {
11839  array = create<array_t>(std::move(value));
11840  }
11841 
11842  void destroy(value_t t) noexcept
11843  {
11844  switch (t)
11845  {
11846  case value_t::object:
11847  {
11848  AllocatorType<object_t> alloc;
11849  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::destroy(alloc, object);
11850  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::deallocate(alloc, object, 1);
11851  break;
11852  }
11853 
11854  case value_t::array:
11855  {
11856  AllocatorType<array_t> alloc;
11857  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::destroy(alloc, array);
11858  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::deallocate(alloc, array, 1);
11859  break;
11860  }
11861 
11862  case value_t::string:
11863  {
11864  AllocatorType<string_t> alloc;
11865  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::destroy(alloc, string);
11866  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::deallocate(alloc, string, 1);
11867  break;
11868  }
11869 
11870  default:
11871  {
11872  break;
11873  }
11874  }
11875  }

12094  template <typename CompatibleType,
12095  typename U = detail::uncvref_t<CompatibleType>,
12096  detail::enable_if_t<
12097  detail::is_compatible_type<basic_json_t, U>::value, int> = 0>
12098  basic_json(CompatibleType && val) noexcept(noexcept(
12099  JSONSerializer<U>::to_json(std::declval<basic_json_t&>(),
12100  std::forward<CompatibleType>(val))))

12105 
12132  template <typename BasicJsonType,
12133  detail::enable_if_t<
12134  detail::is_basic_json<BasicJsonType>::value and not std::is_same<basic_json, BasicJsonType>::value, int> = 0>
12135  basic_json(const BasicJsonType& val)
12136  {
12137  using other_boolean_t = typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t;
12138  using other_number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
12139  using other_number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
12140  using other_number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
12141  using other_string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
12142  using other_object_t = typename BasicJsonType::object_t;
12143  using other_array_t = typename BasicJsonType::array_t;
12144 
12145  switch (val.type())
12146  {
12147  case value_t::boolean:
12148  JSONSerializer<other_boolean_t>::to_json(*this, val.template get<other_boolean_t>());
12149  break;
12150  case value_t::number_float:
12151  JSONSerializer<other_number_float_t>::to_json(*this, val.template get<other_number_float_t>());
12152  break;
12153  case value_t::number_integer:
12154  JSONSerializer<other_number_integer_t>::to_json(*this, val.template get<other_number_integer_t>());
12155  break;
12156  case value_t::number_unsigned:
12157  JSONSerializer<other_number_unsigned_t>::to_json(*this, val.template get<other_number_unsigned_t>());
12158  break;
12159  case value_t::string:
12160  JSONSerializer<other_string_t>::to_json(*this, val.template get_ref<const other_string_t&>());
12161  break;
12162  case value_t::object:
12163  JSONSerializer<other_object_t>::to_json(*this, val.template get_ref<const other_object_t&>());
12164  break;
12165  case value_t::array:
12166  JSONSerializer<other_array_t>::to_json(*this, val.template get_ref<const other_array_t&>());
12167  break;
12168  case value_t::null:
12169  *this = nullptr;
12170  break;
12171  case value_t::discarded:
12172  m_type = value_t::discarded;
12173  break;
12174  }
12175  assert_invariant();
12176  }
12177 
12252  basic_json(initializer_list_t init,
12253  bool type_deduction = true,
12254  value_t manual_type = value_t::array)
12255  {
12256  // check if each element is an array with two elements whose first
12257  // element is a string
12258  bool is_an_object = std::all_of(init.begin(), init.end(),
12259  [](const detail::json_ref<basic_json>& element_ref)
12260  {
12261  return (element_ref->is_array() and element_ref->size() == 2 and (*element_ref)[0].is_string());
12262  });
12263 
12264  // adjust type if type deduction is not wanted
12265  if (not type_deduction)
12266  {
12267  // if array is wanted, do not create an object though possible
12268  if (manual_type == value_t::array)
12269  {
12270  is_an_object = false;
12271  }
12272 
12273  // if object is wanted but impossible, throw an exception
12274  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(manual_type == value_t::object and not is_an_object))
12275  {
12276  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(301, "cannot create object from initializer list"));
12277  }
12278  }
12279 
12280  if (is_an_object)
12281  {
12282  // the initializer list is a list of pairs -> create object
12283  m_type = value_t::object;
12284  m_value = value_t::object;
12285 
12286  std::for_each(init.begin(), init.end(), [this](const detail::json_ref<basic_json>& element_ref)
12287  {
12288  auto element = element_ref.moved_or_copied();
12289  m_value.object->emplace(
12290  std::move(*((*element.m_value.array)[0].m_value.string)),
12291  std::move((*element.m_value.array)[1]));
12292  });
12293  }
12294  else
12295  {
12296  // the initializer list describes an array -> create array
12297  m_type = value_t::array;
12298  m_value.array = create<array_t>(init.begin(), init.end());
12299  }
12300 
12301  assert_invariant();
12302  }
12303 
12341  static basic_json array(initializer_list_t init = {})
12342  {
12343  return basic_json(init, false, value_t::array);
12344  }
12345 
12384  static basic_json object(initializer_list_t init = {})
12385  {
12386  return basic_json(init, false, value_t::object);
12387  }
12388 
12411  basic_json(size_type cnt, const basic_json& val)
12412  : m_type(value_t::array)
12413  {
12414  m_value.array = create<array_t>(cnt, val);
12415  assert_invariant();
12416  }
12417 
12473  template<class InputIT, typename std::enable_if<
12474  std::is_same<InputIT, typename basic_json_t::iterator>::value or
12475  std::is_same<InputIT, typename basic_json_t::const_iterator>::value, int>::type = 0>
12476  basic_json(InputIT first, InputIT last)
12477  {
12478  assert(first.m_object != nullptr);
12479  assert(last.m_object != nullptr);
12480 
12481  // make sure iterator fits the current value
12482  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(first.m_object != last.m_object))
12483  {
12484  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(201, "iterators are not compatible"));
12485  }
12486 
12487  // copy type from first iterator
12488  m_type = first.m_object->m_type;
12489 
12490  // check if iterator range is complete for primitive values
12491  switch (m_type)
12492  {
12493  case value_t::boolean:
12494  case value_t::number_float:
12495  case value_t::number_integer:
12496  case value_t::number_unsigned:
12497  case value_t::string:
12498  {
12499  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not first.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin()
12500  or not last.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_end()))
12501  {
12502  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(204, "iterators out of range"));
12503  }
12504  break;
12505  }
12506 
12507  default:
12508  break;
12509  }
12510 
12511  switch (m_type)
12512  {
12513  case value_t::number_integer:
12514  {
12515  m_value.number_integer = first.m_object->m_value.number_integer;
12516  break;
12517  }
12518 
12519  case value_t::number_unsigned:
12520  {
12521  m_value.number_unsigned = first.m_object->m_value.number_unsigned;
12522  break;
12523  }
12524 
12525  case value_t::number_float:
12526  {
12527  m_value.number_float = first.m_object->m_value.number_float;
12528  break;
12529  }
12530 
12531  case value_t::boolean:
12532  {
12533  m_value.boolean = first.m_object->m_value.boolean;
12534  break;
12535  }
12536 
12537  case value_t::string:
12538  {
12539  m_value = *first.m_object->m_value.string;
12540  break;
12541  }
12542 
12543  case value_t::object:
12544  {
12545  m_value.object = create<object_t>(first.m_it.object_iterator,
12546  last.m_it.object_iterator);
12547  break;
12548  }
12549 
12550  case value_t::array:
12551  {
12552  m_value.array = create<array_t>(first.m_it.array_iterator,
12553  last.m_it.array_iterator);
12554  break;
12555  }
12556 
12557  default:
12558  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(206, "cannot construct with iterators from " +
12559  std::string(first.m_object->type_name())));
12560  }
12561 
12562  assert_invariant();
12563  }
12564 
12565 
12567  // other constructors and destructor //
12569 
12571  basic_json(const detail::json_ref<basic_json>& ref)
12572  : basic_json(ref.moved_or_copied())
12573  {}
12574 
12600  basic_json(const basic_json& other)
12601  : m_type(other.m_type)
12602  {
12603  // check of passed value is valid
12604  other.assert_invariant();
12605 
12606  switch (m_type)
12607  {
12608  case value_t::object:
12609  {
12610  m_value = *other.m_value.object;
12611  break;
12612  }
12613 
12614  case value_t::array:
12615  {
12616  m_value = *other.m_value.array;
12617  break;
12618  }
12619 
12620  case value_t::string:
12621  {
12622  m_value = *other.m_value.string;
12623  break;
12624  }
12625 
12626  case value_t::boolean:
12627  {
12628  m_value = other.m_value.boolean;
12629  break;
12630  }
12631 
12632  case value_t::number_integer:
12633  {
12634  m_value = other.m_value.number_integer;
12635  break;
12636  }
12637 
12638  case value_t::number_unsigned:
12639  {
12640  m_value = other.m_value.number_unsigned;
12641  break;
12642  }
12643 
12644  case value_t::number_float:
12645  {
12646  m_value = other.m_value.number_float;
12647  break;
12648  }
12649 
12650  default:
12651  break;
12652  }
12653 
12654  assert_invariant();
12655  }
12656 
12683  basic_json(basic_json&& other) noexcept
12684  : m_type(std::move(other.m_type)),
12685  m_value(std::move(other.m_value))
12686  {
12687  // check that passed value is valid
12688  other.assert_invariant();
12689 
12690  // invalidate payload
12691  other.m_type = value_t::null;
12692  other.m_value = {};
12693 
12694  assert_invariant();
12695  }
12696 
12720  reference& operator=(basic_json other) noexcept (
12721  std::is_nothrow_move_constructible<value_t>::value and
12722  std::is_nothrow_move_assignable<value_t>::value and
12723  std::is_nothrow_move_constructible<json_value>::value and
12724  std::is_nothrow_move_assignable<json_value>::value
12725  )
12726  {
12727  // check that passed value is valid
12728  other.assert_invariant();
12729 
12730  using std::swap;
12731  swap(m_type, other.m_type);
12732  swap(m_value, other.m_value);
12733 
12734  assert_invariant();
12735  return *this;
12736  }
12737 
12753  ~basic_json() noexcept
12754  {
12755  assert_invariant();
12756  m_value.destroy(m_type);
12757  }

12806  string_t dump(const int indent = -1, const char indent_char = ' ',
12807  const bool ensure_ascii = false) const
12808  {
12809  string_t result;
12810  serializer s(detail::output_adapter<char, string_t>(result), indent_char);
12811 
12812  if (indent >= 0)
12813  {
12814  s.dump(*this, true, ensure_ascii, static_cast<unsigned int>(indent));
12815  }
12816  else
12817  {
12818  s.dump(*this, false, ensure_ascii, 0);
12819  }
12820 
12821  return result;
12822  }

13309  template<typename ReferenceType, typename ThisType>
13310  static ReferenceType get_ref_impl(ThisType& obj)
13311  {
13312  // delegate the call to get_ptr<>()
13313  auto ptr = obj.template get_ptr<typename std::add_pointer<ReferenceType>::type>();
13314 
13315  if (JSON_LIKELY(ptr != nullptr))
13316  {
13317  return *ptr;
13318  }
13319 
13320  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(303, "incompatible ReferenceType for get_ref, actual type is " + std::string(obj.type_name())));
13321  }

13412  template<typename ValueTypeCV, typename ValueType = detail::uncvref_t<ValueTypeCV>,
13413  detail::enable_if_t <
13414  not detail::is_basic_json<ValueType>::value and
13415  detail::has_from_json<basic_json_t, ValueType>::value and
13416  not detail::has_non_default_from_json<basic_json_t, ValueType>::value,
13417  int> = 0>
13418  ValueType get() const noexcept(noexcept(
13419  JSONSerializer<ValueType>::from_json(std::declval<const basic_json_t&>(), std::declval<ValueType&>())))
13420  {
13421  // we cannot static_assert on ValueTypeCV being non-const, because
13422  // there is support for get<const basic_json_t>(), which is why we
13423  // still need the uncvref
13424  static_assert(not std::is_reference<ValueTypeCV>::value,
13425  "get() cannot be used with reference types, you might want to use get_ref()");
13426  static_assert(std::is_default_constructible<ValueType>::value,
13427  "types must be DefaultConstructible when used with get()");
13428 
13429  ValueType ret;
13430  JSONSerializer<ValueType>::from_json(*this, ret);
13431  return ret;
13432  }

13550  template<typename PointerType, typename std::enable_if<
13551  std::is_pointer<PointerType>::value, int>::type = 0>
13552  PointerType get_ptr() noexcept
13553  {
13554  // get the type of the PointerType (remove pointer and const)
13555  using pointee_t = typename std::remove_const<typename
13556  std::remove_pointer<typename
13557  std::remove_const<PointerType>::type>::type>::type;
13558  // make sure the type matches the allowed types
13559  static_assert(
13560  std::is_same<object_t, pointee_t>::value
13561  or std::is_same<array_t, pointee_t>::value
13562  or std::is_same<string_t, pointee_t>::value
13563  or std::is_same<boolean_t, pointee_t>::value
13564  or std::is_same<number_integer_t, pointee_t>::value
13565  or std::is_same<number_unsigned_t, pointee_t>::value
13566  or std::is_same<number_float_t, pointee_t>::value
13567  , "incompatible pointer type");
13568 
13569  // delegate the call to get_impl_ptr<>()
13570  return get_impl_ptr(static_cast<PointerType>(nullptr));
13571  }

13580  constexpr const PointerType get_ptr() const noexcept
13581  {

13583  using pointee_t = typename std::remove_const<typename
13584  std::remove_pointer<typename
13585  std::remove_const<PointerType>::type>::type>::type;
13586  // make sure the type matches the allowed types
13587  static_assert(
13588  std::is_same<object_t, pointee_t>::value
13589  or std::is_same<array_t, pointee_t>::value
13590  or std::is_same<string_t, pointee_t>::value
13591  or std::is_same<boolean_t, pointee_t>::value
13592  or std::is_same<number_integer_t, pointee_t>::value
13593  or std::is_same<number_unsigned_t, pointee_t>::value
13594  or std::is_same<number_float_t, pointee_t>::value
13595  , "incompatible pointer type");

13927  reference operator[](size_type idx)
13928  {
13929  // implicitly convert null value to an empty array
13930  if (is_null())
13931  {
13932  m_type = value_t::array;
13933  m_value.array = create<array_t>();
13934  assert_invariant();
13935  }
13936 
13937  // operator[] only works for arrays
13938  if (JSON_LIKELY(is_array()))
13939  {
13940  // fill up array with null values if given idx is outside range
13941  if (idx >= m_value.array->size())
13942  {
13943  m_value.array->insert(m_value.array->end(),
13944  idx - m_value.array->size() + 1,
13945  basic_json());
13946  }
13947 
13948  return m_value.array->operator[](idx);
13949  }
13950 
13951  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(305, "cannot use operator[] with " + std::string(type_name())));
13952  }
13953

13975  // const operator[] only works for arrays

13977  {

13979  }
13980 
13981  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(305, "cannot use operator[] with " + std::string(type_name())));
13982  }

14210  template<class ValueType, typename std::enable_if<
14211  std::is_convertible<basic_json_t, ValueType>::value, int>::type = 0>
14212  ValueType value(const typename object_t::key_type& key, const ValueType& default_value) const
14213  {
14214  // at only works for objects
14215  if (JSON_LIKELY(is_object()))
14216  {
14217  // if key is found, return value and given default value otherwise
14218  const auto it = find(key);
14219  if (it != end())
14220  {
14221  return *it;
14222  }
14223 
14224  return default_value;
14225  }
14226 
14227  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(306, "cannot use value() with " + std::string(type_name())));
14228  }

14281  std::is_convertible<basic_json_t, ValueType>::value, int>::type = 0>
14282  ValueType value(const json_pointer& ptr, const ValueType& default_value) const
14283  {

14299  }

14442  template<class IteratorType, typename std::enable_if<
14443  std::is_same<IteratorType, typename basic_json_t::iterator>::value or
14444  std::is_same<IteratorType, typename basic_json_t::const_iterator>::value, int>::type
14445  = 0>
14446  IteratorType erase(IteratorType pos)
14447  {
14448  // make sure iterator fits the current value
14449  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(this != pos.m_object))
14450  {
14451  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(202, "iterator does not fit current value"));
14452  }
14453 
14454  IteratorType result = end();
14455 
14456  switch (m_type)
14457  {
14458  case value_t::boolean:
14459  case value_t::number_float:
14460  case value_t::number_integer:
14461  case value_t::number_unsigned:
14462  case value_t::string:
14463  {
14464  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not pos.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin()))
14465  {
14466  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(205, "iterator out of range"));
14467  }
14468 
14469  if (is_string())
14470  {
14471  AllocatorType<string_t> alloc;
14472  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::destroy(alloc, m_value.string);
14473  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::deallocate(alloc, m_value.string, 1);
14474  m_value.string = nullptr;
14475  }
14476 
14477  m_type = value_t::null;
14478  assert_invariant();
14479  break;
14480  }
14481 
14482  case value_t::object:
14483  {
14484  result.m_it.object_iterator = m_value.object->erase(pos.m_it.object_iterator);
14485  break;
14486  }
14487 
14488  case value_t::array:
14489  {
14490  result.m_it.array_iterator = m_value.array->erase(pos.m_it.array_iterator);
14491  break;
14492  }
14493 
14494  default:
14495  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(307, "cannot use erase() with " + std::string(type_name())));
14496  }
14497 
14498  return result;
14499  }
14500 
14547  template<class IteratorType, typename std::enable_if<
14548  std::is_same<IteratorType, typename basic_json_t::iterator>::value or
14549  std::is_same<IteratorType, typename basic_json_t::const_iterator>::value, int>::type
14550  = 0>
14551  IteratorType erase(IteratorType first, IteratorType last)
14552  {
14553  // make sure iterator fits the current value
14554  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(this != first.m_object or this != last.m_object))
14555  {
14556  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(203, "iterators do not fit current value"));
14557  }
14558 
14559  IteratorType result = end();
14560 
14561  switch (m_type)
14562  {
14563  case value_t::boolean:
14564  case value_t::number_float:
14565  case value_t::number_integer:
14566  case value_t::number_unsigned:
14567  case value_t::string:
14568  {
14569  if (JSON_LIKELY(not first.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin()
14570  or not last.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_end()))
14571  {
14572  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(204, "iterators out of range"));
14573  }
14574 
14575  if (is_string())
14576  {
14577  AllocatorType<string_t> alloc;
14578  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::destroy(alloc, m_value.string);
14579  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::deallocate(alloc, m_value.string, 1);
14580  m_value.string = nullptr;
14581  }
14582 
14583  m_type = value_t::null;
14584  assert_invariant();
14585  break;
14586  }
14587 
14588  case value_t::object:
14589  {
14590  result.m_it.object_iterator = m_value.object->erase(first.m_it.object_iterator,
14591  last.m_it.object_iterator);
14592  break;
14593  }
14594 
14595  case value_t::array:
14596  {
14597  result.m_it.array_iterator = m_value.array->erase(first.m_it.array_iterator,
14598  last.m_it.array_iterator);
14599  break;
14600  }
14601 
14602  default:
14603  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(307, "cannot use erase() with " + std::string(type_name())));
14604  }
14605 
14606  return result;
14607  }

15260  return true;

15271  // delegate call to object_t::empty()

15278  return false;

15536  void push_back(basic_json&& val)
15537  {
15538  // push_back only works for null objects or arrays
15539  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not(is_null() or is_array())))
15540  {
15541  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(308, "cannot use push_back() with " + std::string(type_name())));
15542  }
15543 
15544  // transform null object into an array
15545  if (is_null())
15546  {
15547  m_type = value_t::array;
15548  m_value = value_t::array;
15549  assert_invariant();
15550  }
15551 
15552  // add element to array (move semantics)
15553  m_value.array->push_back(std::move(val));
15554  // invalidate object
15555  val.m_type = value_t::null;
15556  }

15563  {

15565  return *this;
15566  }

15682  push_back(typename object_t::value_type(
15683  std::move(key.get_ref<string_t&>()), (init.begin() + 1)->moved_or_copied()));

15722  template<class... Args>
15723  void emplace_back(Args&& ... args)
15724  {

15727  {
15728  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(311, "cannot use emplace_back() with " + std::string(type_name())));
15729  }

15770  template<class... Args>
15771  std::pair<iterator, bool> emplace(Args&& ... args)
15772  {
15773  // emplace only works for null objects or arrays
15774  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not(is_null() or is_object())))
15775  {
15776  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(311, "cannot use emplace() with " + std::string(type_name())));
15777  }
15778 
15779  // transform null object into an object
15780  if (is_null())
15781  {
15782  m_type = value_t::object;
15783  m_value = value_t::object;
15784  assert_invariant();
15785  }
15786 
15787  // add element to array (perfect forwarding)
15788  auto res = m_value.object->emplace(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
15789  // create result iterator and set iterator to the result of emplace
15790  auto it = begin();
15791  it.m_it.object_iterator = res.first;
15792 
15793  // return pair of iterator and boolean
15794  return {it, res.second};
15795  }

15922  iterator insert(const_iterator pos, const_iterator first, const_iterator last)

16065  void update(const_reference j)
16066  {
16067  // implicitly convert null value to an empty object
16068  if (is_null())
16069  {
16070  m_type = value_t::object;
16071  m_value.object = create<object_t>();
16072  assert_invariant();
16073  }
16074 
16075  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not is_object()))
16076  {
16077  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(312, "cannot use update() with " + std::string(type_name())));
16078  }
16079  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_object()))
16080  {
16081  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(312, "cannot use update() with " + std::string(j.type_name())));
16082  }
16083 
16084  for (auto it = j.cbegin(); it != j.cend(); ++it)
16085  {
16086  m_value.object->operator[](it.key()) = it.value();
16087  }
16088  }
16089 
16116  void update(const_iterator first, const_iterator last)
16117  {
16118  // implicitly convert null value to an empty object
16119  if (is_null())
16120  {
16121  m_type = value_t::object;
16122  m_value.object = create<object_t>();
16123  assert_invariant();
16124  }
16125 
16126  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not is_object()))
16127  {
16128  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(312, "cannot use update() with " + std::string(type_name())));
16129  }
16130 
16131  // check if range iterators belong to the same JSON object
16132  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(first.m_object != last.m_object))
16133  {
16134  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(210, "iterators do not fit"));
16135  }
16136 
16137  // passed iterators must belong to objects
16138  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not first.m_object->is_object()
16139  or not last.m_object->is_object()))
16140  {
16141  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(202, "iterators first and last must point to objects"));
16142  }
16143 
16144  for (auto it = first; it != last; ++it)
16145  {
16146  m_value.object->operator[](it.key()) = it.value();
16147  }
16148  }
16149 
16167  void swap(reference other) noexcept (
16168  std::is_nothrow_move_constructible<value_t>::value and
16169  std::is_nothrow_move_assignable<value_t>::value and
16170  std::is_nothrow_move_constructible<json_value>::value and
16171  std::is_nothrow_move_assignable<json_value>::value
16172  )
16173  {
16174  std::swap(m_type, other.m_type);
16175  std::swap(m_value, other.m_value);
16176  assert_invariant();
16177  }
16178 
16199  void swap(array_t& other)
16200  {
16201  // swap only works for arrays
16202  if (JSON_LIKELY(is_array()))
16203  {
16204  std::swap(*(m_value.array), other);
16205  }
16206  else
16207  {
16208  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(310, "cannot use swap() with " + std::string(type_name())));
16209  }
16210  }
16211

16287 
16327  friend bool operator==(const_reference lhs, const_reference rhs) noexcept
16328  {
16329  const auto lhs_type = lhs.type();
16330  const auto rhs_type = rhs.type();
16331 
16332  if (lhs_type == rhs_type)
16333  {
16334  switch (lhs_type)
16335  {
16336  case value_t::array:
16337  return (*lhs.m_value.array == *rhs.m_value.array);
16338 
16339  case value_t::object:
16340  return (*lhs.m_value.object == *rhs.m_value.object);
16341 
16342  case value_t::null:
16343  return true;
16344 
16345  case value_t::string:
16346  return (*lhs.m_value.string == *rhs.m_value.string);
16347 
16348  case value_t::boolean:
16349  return (lhs.m_value.boolean == rhs.m_value.boolean);
16350 
16351  case value_t::number_integer:
16352  return (lhs.m_value.number_integer == rhs.m_value.number_integer);
16353 
16354  case value_t::number_unsigned:
16355  return (lhs.m_value.number_unsigned == rhs.m_value.number_unsigned);
16356 
16357  case value_t::number_float:
16358  return (lhs.m_value.number_float == rhs.m_value.number_float);
16359 
16360  default:
16361  return false;
16362  }
16363  }
16364  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_integer and rhs_type == value_t::number_float)
16365  {
16366  return (static_cast<number_float_t>(lhs.m_value.number_integer) == rhs.m_value.number_float);
16367  }
16368  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_float and rhs_type == value_t::number_integer)
16369  {
16370  return (lhs.m_value.number_float == static_cast<number_float_t>(rhs.m_value.number_integer));
16371  }
16372  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned and rhs_type == value_t::number_float)
16373  {
16374  return (static_cast<number_float_t>(lhs.m_value.number_unsigned) == rhs.m_value.number_float);
16375  }
16376  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_float and rhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned)
16377  {
16378  return (lhs.m_value.number_float == static_cast<number_float_t>(rhs.m_value.number_unsigned));
16379  }
16380  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned and rhs_type == value_t::number_integer)
16381  {
16382  return (static_cast<number_integer_t>(lhs.m_value.number_unsigned) == rhs.m_value.number_integer);
16383  }
16384  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_integer and rhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned)
16385  {
16386  return (lhs.m_value.number_integer == static_cast<number_integer_t>(rhs.m_value.number_unsigned));
16387  }
16388 
16389  return false;
16390  }
16391

16458 
16485  friend bool operator<(const_reference lhs, const_reference rhs) noexcept
16486  {
16487  const auto lhs_type = lhs.type();
16488  const auto rhs_type = rhs.type();
16489 
16490  if (lhs_type == rhs_type)
16491  {
16492  switch (lhs_type)
16493  {
16494  case value_t::array:
16495  return (*lhs.m_value.array) < (*rhs.m_value.array);
16496 
16497  case value_t::object:
16498  return *lhs.m_value.object < *rhs.m_value.object;
16499 
16500  case value_t::null:
16501  return false;
16502 
16503  case value_t::string:
16504  return *lhs.m_value.string < *rhs.m_value.string;
16505 
16506  case value_t::boolean:
16507  return lhs.m_value.boolean < rhs.m_value.boolean;
16508 
16509  case value_t::number_integer:
16510  return lhs.m_value.number_integer < rhs.m_value.number_integer;
16511 
16512  case value_t::number_unsigned:
16513  return lhs.m_value.number_unsigned < rhs.m_value.number_unsigned;
16514 
16515  case value_t::number_float:
16516  return lhs.m_value.number_float < rhs.m_value.number_float;
16517 
16518  default:
16519  return false;
16520  }
16521  }
16522  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_integer and rhs_type == value_t::number_float)
16523  {
16524  return static_cast<number_float_t>(lhs.m_value.number_integer) < rhs.m_value.number_float;
16525  }
16526  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_float and rhs_type == value_t::number_integer)
16527  {
16528  return lhs.m_value.number_float < static_cast<number_float_t>(rhs.m_value.number_integer);
16529  }
16530  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned and rhs_type == value_t::number_float)
16531  {
16532  return static_cast<number_float_t>(lhs.m_value.number_unsigned) < rhs.m_value.number_float;
16533  }
16534  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_float and rhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned)
16535  {
16536  return lhs.m_value.number_float < static_cast<number_float_t>(rhs.m_value.number_unsigned);
16537  }
16538  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_integer and rhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned)
16539  {
16540  return lhs.m_value.number_integer < static_cast<number_integer_t>(rhs.m_value.number_unsigned);
16541  }
16542  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned and rhs_type == value_t::number_integer)
16543  {
16544  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(lhs.m_value.number_unsigned) < rhs.m_value.number_integer;
16545  }
16546 
16547  // We only reach this line if we cannot compare values. In that case,
16548  // we compare types. Note we have to call the operator explicitly,
16549  // because MSVC has problems otherwise.
16550  return operator<(lhs_type, rhs_type);
16551  }

16558  std::is_scalar<ScalarType>::value, int>::type = 0>

16560  {
16561  return (lhs < basic_json(rhs));
16562  }

16753  friend std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& o, const basic_json& j)
16754  {
16755  // read width member and use it as indentation parameter if nonzero
16756  const bool pretty_print = (o.width() > 0);
16757  const auto indentation = (pretty_print ? o.width() : 0);
16758 
16759  // reset width to 0 for subsequent calls to this stream
16760  o.width(0);
16761 
16762  // do the actual serialization
16763  serializer s(detail::output_adapter<char>(o), o.fill());
16764  s.dump(j, pretty_print, false, static_cast<unsigned int>(indentation));
16765  return o;
16766  }

16870  const bool strict = true)
16871  {

17682  template<typename A1, typename A2,
17683  detail::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<detail::input_adapter, A1, A2>::value, int> = 0>
17684  static basic_json from_ubjson(A1 && a1, A2 && a2,

17688  basic_json result;
17689  detail::json_sax_dom_parser<basic_json> sdp(result, allow_exceptions);
17690  const bool res = binary_reader(detail::input_adapter(std::forward<A1>(a1), std::forward<A2>(a2))).sax_parse(input_format_t::ubjson, &sdp, strict);
17691  return res ? result : basic_json(value_t::discarded);
17692  }

17920 
17922  // JSON Patch functions //
17924 
17927 
17975  basic_json patch(const basic_json& json_patch) const
17976  {
17977  // make a working copy to apply the patch to
17978  basic_json result = *this;
17979 
17980  // the valid JSON Patch operations
17981  enum class patch_operations {add, remove, replace, move, copy, test, invalid};
17982 
17983  const auto get_op = [](const std::string & op)
17984  {
17985  if (op == "add")
17986  {
17987  return patch_operations::add;
17988  }
17989  if (op == "remove")
17990  {
17991  return patch_operations::remove;
17992  }
17993  if (op == "replace")
17994  {
17995  return patch_operations::replace;
17996  }
17997  if (op == "move")
17998  {
17999  return patch_operations::move;
18000  }
18001  if (op == "copy")
18002  {
18003  return patch_operations::copy;
18004  }
18005  if (op == "test")
18006  {
18007  return patch_operations::test;
18008  }
18009 
18010  return patch_operations::invalid;
18011  };
18012 
18013  // wrapper for "add" operation; add value at ptr
18014  const auto operation_add = [&result](json_pointer & ptr, basic_json val)
18015  {
18016  // adding to the root of the target document means replacing it
18017  if (ptr.is_root())
18018  {
18019  result = val;
18020  }
18021  else
18022  {
18023  // make sure the top element of the pointer exists
18024  json_pointer top_pointer = ptr.top();
18025  if (top_pointer != ptr)
18026  {
18027  result.at(top_pointer);
18028  }
18029 
18030  // get reference to parent of JSON pointer ptr
18031  const auto last_path = ptr.pop_back();
18032  basic_json& parent = result[ptr];
18033 
18034  switch (parent.m_type)
18035  {
18036  case value_t::null:
18037  case value_t::object:
18038  {
18039  // use operator[] to add value
18040  parent[last_path] = val;
18041  break;
18042  }
18043 
18044  case value_t::array:
18045  {
18046  if (last_path == "-")
18047  {
18048  // special case: append to back
18049  parent.push_back(val);
18050  }
18051  else
18052  {
18053  const auto idx = json_pointer::array_index(last_path);
18054  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(static_cast<size_type>(idx) > parent.size()))
18055  {
18056  // avoid undefined behavior
18057  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(401, "array index " + std::to_string(idx) + " is out of range"));
18058  }
18059  else
18060  {
18061  // default case: insert add offset
18062  parent.insert(parent.begin() + static_cast<difference_type>(idx), val);
18063  }
18064  }
18065  break;
18066  }
18067 
18068  default:
18069  {
18070  // if there exists a parent it cannot be primitive
18071  assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
18072  }
18073  }
18074  }
18075  };
18076 
18077  // wrapper for "remove" operation; remove value at ptr
18078  const auto operation_remove = [&result](json_pointer & ptr)
18079  {
18080  // get reference to parent of JSON pointer ptr
18081  const auto last_path = ptr.pop_back();
18082  basic_json& parent = result.at(ptr);
18083 
18084  // remove child
18085  if (parent.is_object())
18086  {
18087  // perform range check
18088  auto it = parent.find(last_path);
18089  if (JSON_LIKELY(it != parent.end()))
18090  {
18091  parent.erase(it);
18092  }
18093  else
18094  {
18095  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(403, "key '" + last_path + "' not found"));
18096  }
18097  }
18098  else if (parent.is_array())
18099  {
18100  // note erase performs range check
18101  parent.erase(static_cast<size_type>(json_pointer::array_index(last_path)));
18102  }
18103  };
18104 
18105  // type check: top level value must be an array
18106  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not json_patch.is_array()))
18107  {
18108  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(104, 0, "JSON patch must be an array of objects"));
18109  }
18110 
18111  // iterate and apply the operations
18112  for (const auto& val : json_patch)
18113  {
18114  // wrapper to get a value for an operation
18115  const auto get_value = [&val](const std::string & op,
18116  const std::string & member,
18117  bool string_type) -> basic_json &
18118  {
18119  // find value
18120  auto it = val.m_value.object->find(member);
18121 
18122  // context-sensitive error message
18123  const auto error_msg = (op == "op") ? "operation" : "operation '" + op + "'";
18124 
18125  // check if desired value is present
18126  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(it == val.m_value.object->end()))
18127  {
18128  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(105, 0, error_msg + " must have member '" + member + "'"));
18129  }
18130 
18131  // check if result is of type string
18132  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(string_type and not it->second.is_string()))
18133  {
18134  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(105, 0, error_msg + " must have string member '" + member + "'"));
18135  }
18136 
18137  // no error: return value
18138  return it->second;
18139  };
18140 
18141  // type check: every element of the array must be an object
18142  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not val.is_object()))
18143  {
18144  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(104, 0, "JSON patch must be an array of objects"));
18145  }
18146 
18147  // collect mandatory members
18148  const std::string op = get_value("op", "op", true);
18149  const std::string path = get_value(op, "path", true);
18150  json_pointer ptr(path);
18151 
18152  switch (get_op(op))
18153  {
18154  case patch_operations::add:
18155  {
18156  operation_add(ptr, get_value("add", "value", false));
18157  break;
18158  }
18159 
18160  case patch_operations::remove:
18161  {
18162  operation_remove(ptr);
18163  break;
18164  }
18165 
18166  case patch_operations::replace:
18167  {
18168  // the "path" location must exist - use at()
18169  result.at(ptr) = get_value("replace", "value", false);
18170  break;
18171  }
18172 
18173  case patch_operations::move:
18174  {
18175  const std::string from_path = get_value("move", "from", true);
18176  json_pointer from_ptr(from_path);
18177 
18178  // the "from" location must exist - use at()
18179  basic_json v = result.at(from_ptr);
18180 
18181  // The move operation is functionally identical to a
18182  // "remove" operation on the "from" location, followed
18183  // immediately by an "add" operation at the target
18184  // location with the value that was just removed.
18185  operation_remove(from_ptr);
18186  operation_add(ptr, v);
18187  break;
18188  }
18189 
18190  case patch_operations::copy:
18191  {
18192  const std::string from_path = get_value("copy", "from", true);
18193  const json_pointer from_ptr(from_path);
18194 
18195  // the "from" location must exist - use at()
18196  basic_json v = result.at(from_ptr);
18197 
18198  // The copy is functionally identical to an "add"
18199  // operation at the target location using the value
18200  // specified in the "from" member.
18201  operation_add(ptr, v);
18202  break;
18203  }
18204 
18205  case patch_operations::test:
18206  {
18207  bool success = false;
18208  JSON_TRY
18209  {
18210  // check if "value" matches the one at "path"
18211  // the "path" location must exist - use at()
18212  success = (result.at(ptr) == get_value("test", "value", false));
18213  }
18214  JSON_INTERNAL_CATCH (out_of_range&)
18215  {
18216  // ignore out of range errors: success remains false
18217  }
18218 
18219  // throw an exception if test fails
18220  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not success))
18221  {
18222  JSON_THROW(other_error::create(501, "unsuccessful: " + val.dump()));
18223  }
18224 
18225  break;
18226  }
18227 
18228  case patch_operations::invalid:
18229  {
18230  // op must be "add", "remove", "replace", "move", "copy", or
18231  // "test"
18232  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(105, 0, "operation value '" + op + "' is invalid"));
18233  }
18234  }
18235  }
18236 
18237  return result;
18238  }
18239 
18273  static basic_json diff(const basic_json& source, const basic_json& target,
18274  const std::string& path = "")
18275  {
18276  // the patch
18277  basic_json result(value_t::array);
18278 
18279  // if the values are the same, return empty patch
18280  if (source == target)
18281  {
18282  return result;
18283  }
18284 
18285  if (source.type() != target.type())
18286  {
18287  // different types: replace value
18288  result.push_back(
18289  {
18290  {"op", "replace"}, {"path", path}, {"value", target}
18291  });
18292  }
18293  else
18294  {
18295  switch (source.type())
18296  {
18297  case value_t::array:
18298  {
18299  // first pass: traverse common elements
18300  std::size_t i = 0;
18301  while (i < source.size() and i < target.size())
18302  {
18303  // recursive call to compare array values at index i
18304  auto temp_diff = diff(source[i], target[i], path + "/" + std::to_string(i));
18305  result.insert(result.end(), temp_diff.begin(), temp_diff.end());
18306  ++i;
18307  }
18308 
18309  // i now reached the end of at least one array
18310  // in a second pass, traverse the remaining elements
18311 
18312  // remove my remaining elements
18313  const auto end_index = static_cast<difference_type>(result.size());
18314  while (i < source.size())
18315  {
18316  // add operations in reverse order to avoid invalid
18317  // indices
18318  result.insert(result.begin() + end_index, object(
18319  {
18320  {"op", "remove"},
18321  {"path", path + "/" + std::to_string(i)}
18322  }));
18323  ++i;
18324  }
18325 
18326  // add other remaining elements
18327  while (i < target.size())
18328  {
18329  result.push_back(
18330  {
18331  {"op", "add"},
18332  {"path", path + "/" + std::to_string(i)},
18333  {"value", target[i]}
18334  });
18335  ++i;
18336  }
18337 
18338  break;
18339  }
18340 
18341  case value_t::object:
18342  {
18343  // first pass: traverse this object's elements
18344  for (auto it = source.cbegin(); it != source.cend(); ++it)
18345  {
18346  // escape the key name to be used in a JSON patch
18347  const auto key = json_pointer::escape(it.key());
18348 
18349  if (target.find(it.key()) != target.end())
18350  {
18351  // recursive call to compare object values at key it
18352  auto temp_diff = diff(it.value(), target[it.key()], path + "/" + key);
18353  result.insert(result.end(), temp_diff.begin(), temp_diff.end());
18354  }
18355  else
18356  {
18357  // found a key that is not in o -> remove it
18358  result.push_back(object(
18359  {
18360  {"op", "remove"}, {"path", path + "/" + key}
18361  }));
18362  }
18363  }
18364 
18365  // second pass: traverse other object's elements
18366  for (auto it = target.cbegin(); it != target.cend(); ++it)
18367  {
18368  if (source.find(it.key()) == source.end())
18369  {
18370  // found a key that is not in this -> add it
18371  const auto key = json_pointer::escape(it.key());
18372  result.push_back(
18373  {
18374  {"op", "add"}, {"path", path + "/" + key},
18375  {"value", it.value()}
18376  });
18377  }
18378  }
18379 
18380  break;
18381  }
18382 
18383  default:
18384  {
18385  // both primitive type: replace value
18386  result.push_back(
18387  {
18388  {"op", "replace"}, {"path", path}, {"value", target}
18389  });
18390  break;
18391  }
18392  }
18393  }
18394 
18395  return result;
18396  }
18397 
18399 
18401  // JSON Merge Patch functions //
18403 
18406 
18449  void merge_patch(const basic_json& patch)
18450  {
18451  if (patch.is_object())
18452  {
18453  if (not is_object())
18454  {
18455  *this = object();
18456  }
18457  for (auto it = patch.begin(); it != patch.end(); ++it)
18458  {
18459  if (it.value().is_null())
18460  {
18461  erase(it.key());
18462  }
18463  else
18464  {
18465  operator[](it.key()).merge_patch(it.value());
18466  }
18467  }
18468  }
18469  else
18470  {
18471  *this = patch;
18472  }
18473  }
18474 
18476 };
